 loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Correct_Century\" title=\"Correct Century\">Correct Century</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 105 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Correct Century&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Correct+Century\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Cosmic_Era\" title=\"Cosmic Era\">Cosmic Era</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 993 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Cosmic Era&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Cosmic+Era\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Anno_Domini\" title=\"Anno Domini\">Anno Domini</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 365 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Anno Domini&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Anno+Domini\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Advanced_Generation\" title=\"Advanced Generation\">Advanced Generation</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 304 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Advanced Generation&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Advanced+Generation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Build_Fighters\" title=\"Build Fighters\">Build Fighters</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 342 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Build Fighters&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Build+Fighters\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Post_Disaster\" title=\"Post Disaster\">Post Disaster</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 272 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Post Disaster&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Post+Disaster\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li></ul></div>\n</div>\n</aside>\n\n<b>Master Grade</b> (<b>MG</b>)<span style=\"font-weight: normal\"> (<span class=\"t_nihongo_kanji\" lang=\"ja\">\u30de\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30b0\u30ec\u30fc\u30c9</span><span class=\"t_nihongo_comma\" style=\"display:none\">,</span> <i><span class=\"t_nihongo_romaji\">Masut\u0101 Gur\u0113do</span></i><span class=\"t_nihongo_help\"><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Japanese\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Help:Japanese\"><span class=\"t_nihongo_icon\" style=\"color:#00e;font:bold 80% sans-serif;text-decoration:none;padding:0 .1em;\">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> is a line of 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Gunpla\" title=\"Gunpla\">Gunpla</a> kits of the <a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Weapon\" title=\"Mobile Weapon\">Mobile Suits</a> in the <i>Gundam</i> meta series. The series was first produced in 1995 as part of the Gundam 15th Anniversary project.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>1<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup>\n</p><p>Master Grade kits differ from other 1/100 scale Gunpla, with their level of detail, articulation, and proportions being second only to the <a href=\"/wiki/Perfect_Grade\" title=\"Perfect Grade\">Perfect Grade</a> line. A majority of MG kits feature a skeletal inner frame with working hydraulics, some also accommodate Gunpla LED Units for light-up gimmicks. To give viewers a perspective of the Mobile Suit's size, many MG kits come with 1/100 scale figurines of the pilots or key characters of their respective series. In addition, some kits include 1/20 scale character figures.\n</p><p>Beginning in 2002, veteran mecha designer <a href=\"/wiki/Hajime_Katoki\" title=\"Hajime Katoki\">Hajime Katoki</a> began redesigning various Mobile Suits and releasing them in the Master Grade line under the label of \"Ver.Ka\" (Version Katoki). Some of the Ver.Ka kits were produced as a result of annual fan votes. In addition, many Mobile Suits from the <a href=\"/wiki/Universal_Century\" title=\"Universal Century\">Universal Century</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Cosmic_Era\" title=\"Cosmic Era\">Cosmic Era</a> timelines have received redesigns under the monikers \"Ver.1.5\", \"Ver.2.0\", \"Ver.3.0\", and \"Ver.RM\".\n</p><p>In 2020, Bandai created a new sub-line <b>Master Grade Extreme</b> (<b>MGEX</b>),<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>2<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup> which features \"Extreme Points\", additional gimmicks that exaggerate key points of the featured Gundam using custom lighting units, a completely gold washed inner frame or other methods to strongly highlight the uniqueness of the Gundam. The sub-line also has its own Ver.Ka kits, with the first in the line being a Ver Ka.\n</p><p>Aside from the <i>Gundam</i> franchise, the Master Grade line has hosted other mecha anime series such as <i>Aura Battler Dunbine</i> and <i><a href=\"https://patlabor.fandom.com/wiki/\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:c:patlabor\">Mobile Police Patlabor</a></i>. The line also has a spin-off line called Master Grade Figure-rise, which focuses on character kits for anime titles such as <i>Dragon Ball Z</i>, <i>One Piece</i>, and <i>Tiger &amp; Bunny</i>, as well as <i>tokusatsu</i> titles such as <i>Kamen Rider</i>.\n</p><p>Following the reorganization of Bandai Namco Group, box covers of reissue and future release of kits from September 2018 onwards feature a blue Bandai logo instead of the original red logo, while releases and reissues from mid-2022 onwards further feature the Bandai Namco logo on the upper right or lower left corner, further reissues from 2023 onwards some kits are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</p><p>This article covers only the <i>Gundam</i> releases.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Regulars\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Regulars</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Special_Editions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Special Editions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Exclusives\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Exclusives</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Master_Grade_Extreme\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Master Grade Extreme</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Notes_&amp;_Trivia\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes &amp; Trivia</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Regulars\">Regulars</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fgundam.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMaster_Grade%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D1&amp;uselang=en&amp;metadata=article-registration-edit-article-section\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\" aria-label=\"Sign in to edit\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"tabber wds-tabber\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__wrapper with-bottom-border\"><ul class=\"wds-tabs\"><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab wds-is-current\" data-hash=\"1995_\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">1995 </a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"1996\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">1996</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"1997\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">1997</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"1998\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">1998</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"1999\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">1999</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2000\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2000</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2001\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2001</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2002\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2002</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2003\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2003</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2004\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2004</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2005\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2005</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2006\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2006</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2007\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2007</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2008\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2008</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2009\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2009</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2010\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2010</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2011\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2011</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2012\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2012</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2013\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2013</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2014\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2014</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2015\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2015</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2016\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2016</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2017\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2017</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2018\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2018</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2019\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2019</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2020\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2020</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2021\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2021</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2022\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2022</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2023\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2023</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2024\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2024</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2025\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2025</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"2026\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">2026</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"B-Club\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">B-Club</a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"Other\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">Other</a></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content wds-is-current\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>001 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f7/Mg-rx-78-2original.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20240403170157\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78-2original\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78-2original.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78-2original.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f7/Mg-rx-78-2original.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20240403170157\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-2_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-2 Gundam\">Gundam RX-78-2</a>\n</td>\n<td>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1995 July\n</td>\n<td>Features markings pre-printed on shoulder armor parts. Includes transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FF-X7_Core_Fighter\" title=\"FF-X7 Core Fighter\">FF-X7 Core Fighter</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine. First Master Grade kit, also the first Gundam kit to be given the correct designation \"RX-78-2\".\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>002 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e3/Mg-ms06s.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201111409\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms06s\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms06s.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms06s.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e3/Mg-ms06s.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201111409\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06S_Zaku_II_Commander_Type\" title=\"MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type\">MS-06S Zaku II</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1995 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-5. First MG kit with leg inner frame parts.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>003 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6c/Mg-ms06f.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201111651\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms06f\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms06f.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms06f.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6c/Mg-ms06f.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201111651\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06F_Zaku_II\" title=\"MS-06F Zaku II\">MS-06F</a>/<a href=\"/wiki/MS-06J_Zaku_II_Ground_Type\" title=\"MS-06J Zaku II Ground Type\">J</a> Zaku II\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1995 October\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-002. Includes Missile Pods, MMP-80 Machine Gun, Cracker Grenades, and Zeon pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-5.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>004 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/cd/Mg-rx-78-g3.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201112621\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78-g3\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78-g3.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78-g3.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/cd/Mg-rx-78-g3.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201112621\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-3_G-3_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-3 G-3 Gundam\">Gundam RX-78-3</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1996 March\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-001. First MG kit from the <i>MSV</i> series.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>005 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/63/MSZ-006.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20120206082311\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MSZ-006\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"131\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MSZ-006.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"MSZ-006.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/63/MSZ-006.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206082311\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-006_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam\">MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1996 April\n</td>\n<td>Features stabilizer with pre-printed markings and LED light-up gimmick (requires CR1220 battery). Includes Hyper Mega Launcher, Grenade Launcher, and <a href=\"/wiki/Kamille_Bidan\" title=\"Kamille Bidan\">Kamille Bidan</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as <a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Decal\" title=\"Gundam Decal\">GD</a>-1. First transformable MG.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>006 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c2/Mg-ms-06r1-sm.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180831085234\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-06r1-sm\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-06r1-sm.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-06r1-sm.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c2/Mg-ms-06r1-sm.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180831085234\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06R-1A_Zaku_II_High_Mobility_Type\" title=\"MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type\">MS-06R-1 Zaku II (Shin Matsunaga Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>1996 June\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-002. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Shin_Matsunaga\" title=\"Shin Matsunaga\">Shin Matsunaga</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>007 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/76/Ms-06r-2-mg1.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180831085541\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Ms-06r-2-mg1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Ms-06r-2-mg1.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Ms-06r-2-mg1.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/76/Ms-06r-2-mg1.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180831085541\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06R-2_Zaku_II_High_Mobility_Type\" title=\"MS-06R-2 Zaku II High Mobility Type\">MS-06R-2 Zaku II (J. Ridden Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>1996 June\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-006. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Johnny_Ridden\" title=\"Johnny Ridden\">Johnny Ridden</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>008 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bf/Mg-ms14-ca.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206085420\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms14-ca\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"137\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms14-ca.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms14-ca.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bf/Mg-ms14-ca.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206085420\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-14S_Gelgoog_Commander_Type\" title=\"MS-14S Gelgoog Commander Type\">MS-14S Gelgoog (C. Aznable Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1996 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>009 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/78/Mg-ms-14c-jr.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206085515\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-14c-jr\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"137\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-14c-jr.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-14c-jr.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/78/Mg-ms-14c-jr.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206085515\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-14C_Gelgoog_Cannon\" title=\"MS-14C Gelgoog Cannon\">MS-14B/C Gelgoog Cannon (J. Ridden Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1997 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-008. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Johnny_Ridden\" title=\"Johnny Ridden\">Johnny Ridden</a> figurine and parts to create <a href=\"/wiki/MS-14B_Gelgoog_High_Mobility_Type\" title=\"MS-14B Gelgoog High Mobility Type\">MS-14B Gelgoog High Mobility Type</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>010 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1d/Mg-rx-78gp01.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206085635\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78gp01\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78gp01.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78gp01.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1d/Mg-rx-78gp01.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206085635\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78GP01_Gundam_%22Zephyranthes%22\" title=\"RX-78GP01 Gundam &quot;Zephyranthes&quot;\">Gundam GP01</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1997 August\n</td>\n<td>Includes transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FF-XII_Core_Fighter_II\" title=\"FF-XII Core Fighter II\">FF-XII Core Fighter II</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Kou_Uraki\" title=\"Kou Uraki\">Kou Uraki</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24. First Gundam kit with leg inner frame parts.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>011 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/49/Mg-ms14-a.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206085727\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms14-a\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"138\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms14-a.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms14-a.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/49/Mg-ms14-a.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206085727\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-14A_Gelgoog\" title=\"MS-14A Gelgoog\">MS-14A Gelgoog</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1997 September\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-008. Uses modified A plate runner of MG-009. Beam Rifle replaced by Beam Machine Gun. Includes Zeon pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>012 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a4/Mg-rx-78gp01fb.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201113757\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78gp01fb\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78gp01fb.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78gp01fb.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a4/Mg-rx-78gp01fb.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201113757\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78GP01-Fb_Gundam_Full_Burnern_%22Zephyranthes%22\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RX-78GP01-Fb Gundam Full Burnern &quot;Zephyranthes&quot;\">Gundam GP01Fb</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1997 December\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-010. Includes transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FF-XII-Fb_Core_Fighter_II_Full_Burnern\" title=\"FF-XII-Fb Core Fighter II Full Burnern\">FF-XII-Fb Core Fighter II Full Burnern</a>. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\