a-image-name=\"Mg-rx-178mk-ii.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-178mk-ii.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/93/Mg-rx-178mk-ii.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180829174752\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-178_Gundam_Mk-II\" title=\"RX-178 Gundam Mk-II\">RX-178 Gundam Mk-II (A.E.U.G.)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>1998 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Kamille_Bidan\" title=\"Kamille Bidan\">Kamille Bidan</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-6.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>015 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/85/Mg-rx-178t.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151104030319\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-178t\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"152\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-178t.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-178t.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/85/Mg-rx-178t.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151104030319\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-178_Gundam_Mk-II\" title=\"RX-178 Gundam Mk-II\">RX-178 Gundam Mk-II (Titans)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>1998 August\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-014. Includes Titans pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-7.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>016 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ab/Mg-rx-178-fxa-05.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201114743\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-178-fxa-05\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-178-fxa-05.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-178-fxa-05.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ab/Mg-rx-178-fxa-05.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201114743\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-178%2BFXA-05D_Super_Gundam\" title=\"RX-178+FXA-05D Super Gundam\">FXA-05D/RX-178 Super Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>1998 December\n</td>\n<td>Re-release of MG-014 with fully transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FXA-05D_G-Defenser\" title=\"FXA-05D G-Defenser\">FXA-05D G-Defenser</a>, which is also compatible with MG-082. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-7.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>017 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7b/Mg-rgm-79.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201115250\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rgm-79\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"152\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rgm-79.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rgm-79.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7b/Mg-rgm-79.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201115250\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79_GM\" title=\"RGM-79 GM\">RGM-79 GM</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1999 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-001. Includes detachable cockpit block and Earth Federation pilot figurine. First MG kit to replace \"U.N.T. Spacy\" with \"E.F.S.F.\" as the official <a href=\"/wiki/Earth_Federation_Forces\" title=\"Earth Federation Forces\">Earth Federation Forces</a> moniker.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>018 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e0/Mg-ms-05b.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206090000\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-05b\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"153\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-05b.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-05b.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e0/Mg-ms-05b.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206090000\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-05B_Zaku_I\" title=\"MS-05B Zaku I\">MS-05B Zaku I</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1999 May\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-002. First MG kit to replace \"Zeon Dukedom\" with the official moniker <a href=\"/wiki/Principality_of_Zeon\" title=\"Principality of Zeon\">Principality of Zeon</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>019 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7d/Mg-ms-05bt.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206172810\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-05bt\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"153\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-05bt.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-05bt.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7d/Mg-ms-05bt.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206172810\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-05B_Zaku_I\" title=\"MS-05B Zaku I\">MS-05B Zaku I (Black Tri-Stars)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>1999 May\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-018. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Tri-Stars\" title=\"Black Tri-Stars\">Gaia</a> figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>020 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2f/Ms-06r1a-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110919190723\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Ms-06r1a-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"151\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Ms-06r1a-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Ms-06r1a-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2f/Ms-06r1a-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110919190723\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06R-1A_Zaku_II_High_Mobility_Type\" title=\"MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type\">MS-06R-1A Zaku II (Black Tri-Stars)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1999 June\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-006; K plate runner with leg armor parts replaced by P plate runner with Giant Bazooka and Shield parts. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Tri-Stars\" title=\"Black Tri-Stars\">Mash</a> figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>021 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/29/Mg-ms-09.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201115938\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-09\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-09.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-09.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/29/Mg-ms-09.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201115938\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-09_Dom\" title=\"MS-09 Dom\">MS-09 Dom</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>1999 June\n</td>\n<td>Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Tri-Stars\" title=\"Black Tri-Stars\">Ortega</a> figures. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-15.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>022 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/97/Mg-alex.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20191107074848\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-alex\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-alex.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-alex.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/97/Mg-alex.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20191107074848\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78NT-1_Gundam_NT-1\" title=\"RX-78NT-1 Gundam NT-1\">Gundam RX-78 NT-1</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0080:_War_in_the_Pocket\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1999 June\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Christina_Mackenzie\" title=\"Christina Mackenzie\">Christina Mackenzie</a> figurine and detachable Chobham Armor. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-53.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>023 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/Mg-ms-09r.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201120117\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-09r\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"124\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-09r.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-09r.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/Mg-ms-09r.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201120117\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-09R_Rick_Dom\" title=\"MS-09R Rick Dom\">MS-09R Rick-Dom</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>1999 October\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-021; G and L plate runners replaced by N and O plate runners. Includes Zeon pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-15.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>024 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0c/Rgm-79n-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120127135556\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Rgm-79n-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"153\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Rgm-79n-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Rgm-79n-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0c/Rgm-79n-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120127135556\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79N_GM_Custom\" title=\"RGM-79N GM Custom\">RGM-79N GM Custom</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1999 December\n</td>\n<td>Uses the B plate runner of MG-022. Includes 90mm Machine Gun as seen in <a href=\"/wiki/Into_Battle,_Albion!\" title=\"Into Battle, Albion!\">episode 3</a> of the OVA, and 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/South_Burning\" title=\"South Burning\">South Burning</a> figures. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>025 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8b/Rgm-79q-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120127135954\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Rgm-79q-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"153\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Rgm-79q-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Rgm-79q-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8b/Rgm-79q-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120127135954\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79Q_GM_Quel\" title=\"RGM-79Q GM Quel\">RGM-79Q GM Quel</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>1999 December\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-024. Includes Beam Rifle, 1/20 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Nina_Purpleton\" title=\"Nina Purpleton\">Nina Purpleton</a> figure and 1/100 scale Titans pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>026 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/15/Msz-010-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120127140317\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Msz-010-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Msz-010-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Msz-010-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/15/Msz-010-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120127140317\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-010_%CE%96%CE%96_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-010 \u0396\u0396 Gundam\">MSZ-010 \u0396\u0396 Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_ZZ\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ\">Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>1999 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FXA-07GB_Neo_Core_Fighter\" title=\"FXA-07GB Neo Core Fighter\">FXA-07GB Neo Core Fighter</a>, semi-transformable Core Block, and <a href=\"/wiki/Judau_Ashta\" title=\"Judau Ashta\">Judau Ashta</a> figurine. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>027 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/51/Mg-rx-79g.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201121137\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-79g\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-79g.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-79g.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/51/Mg-rx-79g.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201121137\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-79%EF%BC%BBG%EF%BC%BD_Gundam_Ground_Type\" title=\"RX-79\uff3bG\uff3d Gundam Ground Type\">RX-79\uff3bG\uff3d Gundam Ground Type</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_08th_MS_Team\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2000 May\n</td>\n<td>Includes Weapon Rack and <a href=\"/wiki/Shiroh_Amada\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shiroh Amada\">Shiroh Amada</a> figurine. First Gundam kit with arm inner frame parts. Uses Manipulator 1 (MP1) plate runner, a universal runner for the hands of MG ground type EFSF mobile suits.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>028 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/76/RX_78-2_gundam.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20120201181112\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"RX 78-2 gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"RX 78-2 gundam.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"RX_78-2_gundam.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/76/RX_78-2_gundam.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201181112\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-2_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-2 Gundam\">Gundam RX-78-2 Ver.1.5</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2000 June\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-001. Features pre-assembled legs and waist inner frame. Includes Beam Javelin and Gundam Hammer. Only MG kit to be designated as \"Ver.1.5\". Released as part of the Gundam 20th Anniversary Big Bang Project.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>029 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1e/Mg-msn-04.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201121543\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msn-04\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"55\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msn-04.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msn-04.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1e/Mg-msn-04.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201121543\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-04_Sazabi\" title=\"MSN-04 Sazabi\">MSN-04 Sazabi</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a58,000\n</td>\n<td>2000 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-23.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>030 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/48/Fa-010s-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120127140531\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Fa-010s-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Fa-010s-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Fa-010s-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/48/Fa-010s-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120127140531\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/FA-010S_Full_Armor_ZZ_Gundam\" title=\"FA-010S Full Armor ZZ Gundam\">FA-010S Full Armor ZZ Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_ZZ\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ\">Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2000 August\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-026. Removal of Full Armor parts reveals <a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-010S_Enhanced_ZZ_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-010S Enhanced ZZ Gundam\">MSZ-010S Enhanced ZZ Gundam</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>031 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/64/Ms-05b-rb.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206090111\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Ms-05b-rb\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"152\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Ms-05b-rb.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Ms-05b-rb.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/64/Ms-05b-rb.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206090111\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-05B_Zaku_I\" title=\"MS-05B Zaku I\">MS-05B Zaku I (Ramba Ral Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>2000 September\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-018. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Ramba_Ral\" title=\"Ramba Ral\">Ramba Ral</a> figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>032 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e9/Mg-ms07b.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206090251\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms07b\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"153\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms07b.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms07b.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e9/Mg-ms07b.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206090251\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-07B_Gouf\" title=\"MS-07B Gouf\">MS-07B Gouf</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>2000 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes 1/20 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Crowley_Hamon\" title=\"Crowley Hamon\">Crowley Hamon</a> figure and 1/100 scale Ramba Ral figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-10.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>033 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2d/Mg-rx-79g-ez8.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201121959\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-79g-ez8\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-79g-ez8.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-79g-ez8.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2d/Mg-rx-79g-ez8.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201121959\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-79%EF%BC%BBG%EF%BC%BDEz-8_Gundam_Ez8\" title=\"RX-79\uff3bG\uff3dEz-8 Gundam Ez8\">Gundam Ez8</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_08th_MS_Team\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2000 October\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-027. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Shiro_Amada\" title=\"Shiro Amada\">Shiro Amada</a> figures. Uses Manipulator 1 (MP1) plate runner.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>034 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5d/Rx-93-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120127164809\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Rx-93-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Rx-93-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Rx-93-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5d/Rx-93-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120127164809\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-93_%CE%BD_Gundam\" title=\"RX-93 \u03bd Gundam\">RX-93 \u03bd Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2000 December\n</td>\n<td>Features diecast metal parts for the ankles and hips. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-23. First Gundam kit with torso inner frame parts.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>035 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3d/Mg-ms-18e.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202040807\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-18e\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-18e.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-18e.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3d/Mg-ms-18e.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202040807\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-18E_K%C3%A4mpfer\" title=\"MS-18E K\u00e4mpfer\">MS-18E K\u00e4mpfer</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0080:_War_in_the_Pocket\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 January\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Mikhail_Kaminsky\" title=\"Mikhail Kaminsky\">Mikhail Kaminsky</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-54. Uses Manipulator 2 (MP2) plate runner, a universal hand runner for MG ground-type Principality of Zeon kits.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>036 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/ba/Mg-ms-07b3.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201141912\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-07b3\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"158\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-07b3.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-07b3.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/ba/Mg-ms-07b3.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201141912\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-07B-3_Gouf_Custom\" title=\"MS-07B-3 Gouf Custom\">MS-07B-3 Gouf Custom</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_08th_MS_Team\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 February\n</td>\n<td>Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Norris_Packard\" title=\"Norris Packard\">Norris Packard</a> figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>037 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/84/Mg-msn-001.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201151954\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msn-001\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msn-001.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msn-001.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/84/Mg-msn-001.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201151954\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-00100_Hyaku_Shiki\" title=\"MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki\">MSN-00100 Hyaku-Shiki</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2001 March\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Quattro Bajeena</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-8. First regular released chrome plated MG kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>038 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d2/Mg-rx-78gp03s.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201122309\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78gp03s\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78gp03s.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78gp03s.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d2/Mg-rx-78gp03s.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201122309\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78GP03S_Gundam_%22Dendrobium_Stamen%22\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RX-78GP03S Gundam &quot;Dendrobium Stamen&quot;\">Gundam GP03S</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2001 April\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Kou_Uraki\" title=\"Kou Uraki\">Kou Uraki</a> figurine and transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FF-XII_Core_Fighter_II\" title=\"FF-XII Core Fighter II\">FF-XII-Sp Core Fighter II-Sp</a>, which can be swapped with the Linear Seat type block. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>039 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/83/Mg-rgz-91.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201135923\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rgz-91\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rgz-91.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rgz-91.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/83/Mg-rgz-91.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201135923\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGZ-91_Re-GZ\" title=\"RGZ-91 Re-GZ\">RGZ-91 Re-GZ</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 June\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine and display stand for Wave Rider mode or Back Weapon System. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-23.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>040 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/87/Mg-rgm-79g.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206090524\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rgm-79g\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rgm-79g.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rgm-79g.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/87/Mg-rgm-79g.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206090524\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79%EF%BC%BBG%EF%BC%BD_GM_Ground_Type\" title=\"RGM-79\uff3bG\uff3d GM Ground Type\">RGM-79[G] GM</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_08th_MS_Team\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 July\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-027. Uses Manipulator 1 (MP1) plate runner.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>041 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1f/Mg-amx-004.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202040935\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-amx-004\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"128\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-amx-004.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-amx-004.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1f/Mg-amx-004.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202040935\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AMX-004_Qubeley\" title=\"AMX-004 Qubeley\">AMX-004 Qubeley</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 August\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Haman_Karn\" title=\"Haman Karn\">Haman Karn</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>042 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4c/Hobby_257_pmaster_grade_mg_1100_scale_fa010a_fazz_sentinel_versionp.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206093612\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Hobby 257 pmaster grade mg 1100 scale fa010a fazz sentinel versionp\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Hobby 257 pmaster grade mg 1100 scale fa010a fazz sentinel versionp.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Hobby_257_pmaster_grade_mg_1100_scale_fa010a_fazz_sentinel_versionp.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4c/Hobby_257_pmaster_grade_mg_1100_scale_fa010a_fazz_sentinel_versionp.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206093612\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/FA-010A_FAZZ\" title=\"FA-010A FAZZ\">FA-010-A FAZZ</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 September\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-030. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-21.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>043 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9e/Mg-msz-006a1.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206090635\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msz-006a1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msz-006a1.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msz-006a1.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9e/Mg-msz-006a1.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206090635\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-006A1_Zeta_Plus_A1\" title=\"MSZ-006A1 Zeta Plus A1\">MSZ-006A1 Zeta plus</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Karaba\" title=\"Karaba\">Karaba</a> pilot figurine. Fully transformable kit. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-21.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>044 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5b/Mg-g-gundam.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150328025321\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-g-gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-g-gundam.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-g-gundam.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5b/Mg-g-gundam.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150328025321\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GF13-017NJII_God_Gundam\" title=\"GF13-017NJII God Gundam\">GF13-017NJII <i><b>G</b></i> Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Fighter_G_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Fighter G Gundam\">Mobile Fighter G Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>2001 November\n</td>\n<td>Uses \"Action Frame\" to increase articulation and posing. Includes two clear orange \"God Finger\" hands, transformable Core Lander and 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Domon_Kasshu\" title=\"Domon Kasshu\">Domon Kasshu</a> figures. First MG kit from the <a href=\"/wiki/Future_Century\" title=\"Future Century\">Future Century</a> timeline.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>045 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/54/Mg-rx77.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206091037\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx77\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"158\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx77.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx77.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/54/Mg-rx77.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206091037\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-77-2_Guncannon\" title=\"RX-77-2 Guncannon\">RX-77-2 Guncannon</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2001 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes Spray Missiles, transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FF-X7_Core_Fighter\" title=\"FF-X7 Core Fighter\">FF-X7 Core Fighter</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Kai_Shiden\" title=\"Kai Shiden\">Kai Shiden</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-12.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>046 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/70/Mg-msz-006c1.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201140143\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msz-006c1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"140\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msz-006c1.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msz-006c1.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/70/Mg-msz-006c1.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201140143\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-006C1_Zeta_Plus_C1\" title=\"MSZ-006C1 Zeta Plus C1\">MSZ-006C1 Zeta plus C1</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2002 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-043. Includes Earth Federation pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-21. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>047 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/77/MG_-_GF13-001NHII_Master_Gundam_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20250307053218\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - GF13-001NHII Master Gundam - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - GF13-001NHII Master Gundam - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_GF13-001NHII_Master_Gundam_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/77/MG_-_GF13-001NHII_Master_Gundam_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20250307053218\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GF13-001NHII_Master_Gundam\" title=\"GF13-001NHII Master Gundam\">GF13-001NHII Master Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Fighter_G_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Fighter G Gundam\">Mobile Fighter G Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>2002 March\n</td>\n<td>Uses \"Action Frame\" to increase articulation and posing. Includes metal wires for \"Distant Crusher\" poses, four clear red \"Darkness Finger\" hands (one for MG-044 to replicate a battle scene from the series), and 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Master_Asia\" title=\"Master Asia\">Master Asia</a> figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>048 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d1/Mg-ms-06f2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201112155\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-06f2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-06f2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-06f2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d1/Mg-ms-06f2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201112155\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06F2_Zaku_II_F2_Type\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 Type\">MS-06F-2 Zaku II F2 (Zeon)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2002 April\n</td>\n<td>Includes Missile Pods, MMP-80 Machine Gun, and Zeon pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>049 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/14/MG-Gundam-GF13-017NJ-Shining-Gundam-Box-Art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20191107075424\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG-Gundam-GF13-017NJ-Shining-Gundam-Box-Art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG-Gundam-GF13-017NJ-Shining-Gundam-Box-Art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG-Gundam-GF13-017NJ-Shining-Gundam-Box-Art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/14/MG-Gundam-GF13-017NJ-Shining-Gundam-Box-Art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20191107075424\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GF13-017NJ_Shining_Gundam\" title=\"GF13-017NJ Shining Gundam\">GF13-017NJ Shining Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Fighter_G_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Fighter G Gundam\">Mobile Fighter G Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>2002 May\n</td>\n<td>Uses \"Action Frame\" to increase articulation and posing. Includes two clear green \"Shining Finger\" hands, transformable Core Lander, and 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Domon_Kasshu\" title=\"Domon Kasshu\">Domon Kasshu</a> (in Mobile Trace System suit) figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>050 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e8/Mg-rgm79-c-earth.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206092019\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rgm79-c-earth\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rgm79-c-earth.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rgm79-c-earth.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e8/Mg-rgm79-c-earth.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206092019\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79C_GM_Kai\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RGM-79C GM Kai\">RGM-79C GM Type C (Earth Type)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>2002 June\n</td>\n<td>Features modular gun that can be converted into 90mm Machine Gun or GM Rifle. Includes Beam Spray Gun, detachable cockpit block, and Earth Federation pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>051 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/84/Mg-msn-02.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201140604\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msn-02\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msn-02.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msn-02.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/84/Mg-msn-02.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201140604\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-02_Zeong\" title=\"MSN-02 Zeong\">MSN-02 Zeong</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2002 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes display stands (for unit and arms) and <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>052 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/Mg-rx-78ca.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201144155\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78ca\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"152\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78ca.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78ca.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/Mg-rx-78ca.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201144155\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78/C.A._Gundam_Char_Aznable_Custom\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RX-78/C.A. Gundam Char Aznable Custom\">Gundam RX-78/C.A.</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Gihren%27s_Greed\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Gihren&#39;s Greed\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Gihren's Greed</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2002 August\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-028. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>053 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/56/Mg-spiegel.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202041352\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-spiegel\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-spiegel.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-spiegel.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/56/Mg-spiegel.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202041352\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GF13-021NG_Gundam_Spiegel\" title=\"GF13-021NG Gundam Spiegel\">GF13-021NG Gundam Spiegel</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Fighter_G_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Fighter G Gundam\">Mobile Fighter G Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>2002 August\n</td>\n<td>Uses \"Action Frame\" to increase articulation and posing. Features collapsible chest to allow crossed arm poses. Includes transformable Core Lander and 1/20 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Schwarz_Bruder\" title=\"Schwarz Bruder\">Schwarz Bruder</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Rain_Mikamura\" title=\"Rain Mikamura\">Rain Mikamura</a> (with two different head sculpts) figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>054 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c8/MG_MS-06F2_Zaku_II_F2_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20101211124307\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_MS-06F2_Zaku_II_F2_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c8/MG_MS-06F2_Zaku_II_F2_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20101211124307\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06F2_Zaku_II_F2_Type\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 Type\">MS-06F-2 Zaku II F2 (E.F.S.F)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2002 September\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-048 with new head armor; Missile Pods and MMP-80 Machine Gun replaced by MMP-78 Machine Gun and Heat Hawk. Includes Earth Federation pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>055 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/fe/Mg-msa-011s.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201143117\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msa-011s\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msa-011s.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msa-011s.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/fe/Mg-msa-011s.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201143117\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSA-0011_S_Gundam\" title=\"MSA-0011 S Gundam\">MSA-0011 S-Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2002 October\n</td>\n<td>Fully transformable kit. Includes Core Fighter and G-Core. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-21.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>056 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/68/Mg-rgm79-c-space.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206092143\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rgm79-c-space\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rgm79-c-space.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rgm79-c-space.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/68/Mg-rgm79-c-space.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206092143\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79C_GM_Kai\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RGM-79C GM Kai\">RGM-79C GM Type C (Space Type)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,500\n</td>\n<td>2002 November\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-050. Includes parts to create Long Rifle. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>057 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/af/Mg-rx78-ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206092248\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx78-ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx78-ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx78-ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/af/Mg-rx78-ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206092248\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-2_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-2 Gundam\">RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.Ka</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,200\n</td>\n<td>2002 December\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-050. Includes a non-transformable Core Block and MG-050's cockpit block. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-2. First release of a MS redesigned by <a href=\"/wiki/Hajime_Katoki\" title=\"Hajime Katoki\">Hajime Katoki</a>. First Gundam kit to have a fully transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FF-X7_Core_Fighter\" title=\"FF-X7 Core Fighter\">FF-X7 Core Fighter</a> with a collapsible tail fin.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>058 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8b/MG_Rick_Dom_C.A._Custom.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201143326\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Rick Dom C.A. Custom\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Rick Dom C.A. Custom.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Rick_Dom_C.A._Custom.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8b/MG_Rick_Dom_C.A._Custom.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201143326\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-09RS_Rick_Dom\" title=\"MS-09RS Rick Dom\">MS-09RS Rick-Dom (Char Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_(Novel)\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam (Novel)\">Mobile Suit Gundam (Novel)</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2003 January\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-021. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>059 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/ff/Mg-ms14-ag.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206172943\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms14-ag\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms14-ag.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms14-ag.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/ff/Mg-ms14-ag.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206172943\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-14A_Gelgoog\" title=\"MS-14A Gelgoog\">MS-14A Gelgoog (Anavel Gato Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0083:_Stardust_Memory\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2003 February\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-008. Includes Prototype Beam Rifle, and 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Anavel_Gato\" title=\"Anavel Gato\">Anavel Gato</a> figures. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-24.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>060 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1f/Mg-ext-s.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202041647\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ext-s\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"54\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ext-s.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ext-s.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1f/Mg-ext-s.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202041647\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSA-0011%EF%BC%BBExt%EF%BC%BD_Ex-S_Gundam\" title=\"MSA-0011\uff3bExt\uff3d Ex-S Gundam\">MSA-0011[Ext] Ex-S Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a58,000\n</td>\n<td>2003 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-055. Includes display base for Gundam and Core Fighter. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-21. Transforms via complex parts-forming.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>061 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/Mg-zgok.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201143541\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-zgok\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"139\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-zgok.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-zgok.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/Mg-zgok.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201143541\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSM-07_Z%27Gok\" title=\"MSM-07 Z&#39;Gok\">MSM-07 Z'Gok</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2003 May\n</td>\n<td>Features rubber parts at certain joints. Includes Zeon pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>062 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2e/Mg-gogg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201143737\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-gogg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-gogg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-gogg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2e/Mg-gogg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201143737\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSM-03_Gogg\" title=\"MSM-03 Gogg\">MSM-03 Gogg</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2003 June\n</td>\n<td>Features foldable arms for cruising mode. Includes Zeon pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>063 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4b/Mg-rx-78-4.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201145318\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78-4\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78-4.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78-4.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4b/Mg-rx-78-4.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201145318\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-4_Gundam_Unit_4_%22G04%22\" title=\"RX-78-4 Gundam Unit 4 &quot;G04&quot;\">RX-78-4 Gundam G04</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Side_Story:_Space,_To_the_End_of_a_Flash\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash\">Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>2003 July\n</td>\n<td>Features no inner frame. Includes booster equipment, Mega Beam Launcher, and <a href=\"/wiki/Ruce_Cassel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ruce Cassel\">Ruce Cassel</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>064 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/86/Mg-rx78g05.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206092401\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx78g05\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx78g05.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx78g05.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/86/Mg-rx78g05.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206092401\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-5_Gundam_Unit_5_%22G05%22\" title=\"RX-78-5 Gundam Unit 5 &quot;G05&quot;\">RX-78-5 Gundam G05</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Side_Story:_Space,_To_the_End_of_a_Flash\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash\">Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>2003 August\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-063. Includes booster equipment, Gatling Gun, and <a href=\"/wiki/Forud_Romfellow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Forud Romfellow\">Forud Romfellow</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>065 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a8/Mg-aile-strike.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202041749\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-aile-strike\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-aile-strike.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-aile-strike.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a8/Mg-aile-strike.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202041749\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105%2BAQM/E-X01_Aile_Strike_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105+AQM/E-X01 Aile Strike Gundam\">GAT-X105 Aile Strike Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2003 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Kira_Yamato\" title=\"Kira Yamato\">Kira Yamato</a> figurine and display base to replicate the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Archangel-class\" title=\"Archangel-class\">Archangel</a></i> launch pad. First MG kit from the <a href=\"/wiki/Cosmic_Era\" title=\"Cosmic Era\">Cosmic Era</a> timeline.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>066 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2a/Mg-msm-07s-ca.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206173042\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msm-07s-ca\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"138\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msm-07s-ca.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msm-07s-ca.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2a/Mg-msm-07s-ca.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206173042\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSM-07S_Z%27Gok_Commander_Type\" title=\"MSM-07S Z&#39;Gok Commander Type\">MSM-07S Z'Gok (Char Aznable Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2003 November\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-061.  Features option to use three-claw or four-claw hands. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>067 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/85/MG_Perfect_Gundam.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20171231022324\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Perfect Gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Perfect Gundam.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Perfect_Gundam.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/85/MG_Perfect_Gundam.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20171231022324\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/PF-78-1_Perfect_Gundam\" title=\"PF-78-1 Perfect Gundam\">PF-78-1 Perfect Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Plamo-Kyoshiro\" title=\"Plamo-Kyoshiro\">Plamo-Kyoshiro</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2003 December\n</td>\n<td>Removal of parts reveals an anime-accurate <a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-2_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-2 Gundam\">RX-78-2 Gundam</a>. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Shiro_Kyoda\" title=\"Shiro Kyoda\">Shiro Kyoda</a> figures. Instruction manual features a <i>Plamo-Kyoshiro</i> manga.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>068 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7f/Mg-amx-004mkii.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151203030612\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-amx-004mkii\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-amx-004mkii.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-amx-004mkii.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7f/Mg-amx-004mkii.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151203030612\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AMX-004_Qubeley_Mk-II\" title=\"AMX-004 Qubeley Mk-II\">AMX-004-3 Qubeley Mk-II</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_ZZ\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ\">Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2004 February\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-041. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Ple_Two\" title=\"Ple Two\">Ple Two</a> figures and custom decals designed by Pepper Shop.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>069 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b6/Mg-wing-verka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201142557\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-wing-verka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"129\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-wing-verka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-wing-verka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b6/Mg-wing-verka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201142557\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01W_Wing_Gundam_EW\" title=\"XXXG-01W Wing Gundam EW\">XXXG-01W Wing Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Endless Waltz\">Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Endless Waltz</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2004 March\n</td>\n<td>Fully transformable kit. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Heero_Yuy\" title=\"Heero Yuy\">Heero Yuy</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-13. First MG kit from the <a href=\"/wiki/After_Colony\" title=\"After Colony\">After Colony</a> timeline.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>070 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1d/Mg-rms-099.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201153005\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rms-099\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rms-099.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rms-099.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1d/Mg-rms-099.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201153005\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RMS-099_Rick_Dias\" title=\"RMS-099 Rick Dias\">RMS-099 Rick Dias</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2004 May\n</td>\n<td>Includes A.E.U.G. pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-11.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>071 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/16/Mg-msn-02-perfect.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201140851\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msn-02-perfect\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msn-02-perfect.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msn-02-perfect.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/16/Mg-msn-02-perfect.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201140851\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-02_Perfect_Zeong\" title=\"MSN-02 Perfect Zeong\">MSN-02 Perfect Zeong</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Plamo-Kyoshiro\" title=\"Plamo-Kyoshiro\">Plamo-Kyoshiro</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a510,000\n</td>\n<td>2004 June\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-051.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>072 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7f/Gundam_Freedom.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20120201144713\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Gundam Freedom\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Gundam Freedom.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"Gundam_Freedom.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7f/Gundam_Freedom.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201144713\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X10A_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2004 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes display base and <a href=\"/wiki/Kira_Yamato\" title=\"Kira Yamato\">Kira Yamato</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-3.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>073 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/Mg-rms-106.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206092831\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rms-106\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rms-106.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rms-106.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/Mg-rms-106.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206092831\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RMS-106_Hizack\" title=\"RMS-106 Hizack\">RMS-106 Hi-Zack</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2004 August\n</td>\n<td>Includes Beam Rifle, Heat Hawk, Beam Saber, Missile Pod, and <a href=\"/wiki/Jerid_Messa\" title=\"Jerid Messa\">Jerid Messa</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-6.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>074 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0b/Mg-strike-rouge.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202042204\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-strike-rouge\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-strike-rouge.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-strike-rouge.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0b/Mg-strike-rouge.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202042204\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MBF-02_Strike_Rouge\" title=\"MBF-02 Strike Rouge\">MBF-02 Strike Rouge</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2004 September\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-065. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Cagalli_Yula_Athha\" title=\"Cagalli Yula Athha\">Cagalli Yula Athha</a> figures.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>075 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b3/Mg-zero-w-2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202042058\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-zero-w-2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"138\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-zero-w-2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-zero-w-2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b3/Mg-zero-w-2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202042058\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-00W0_Wing_Gundam_Zero_EW\" title=\"XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero EW\">XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Endless Waltz\">Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Endless Waltz</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2004 October\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-069. Includes adjustable display base.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>076 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f0/Mg-rb79-ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20250307053306\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rb79-ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"158\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rb79-ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rb79-ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f0/Mg-rb79-ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20250307053306\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RB-79C_Ball_Type_C\" title=\"RB-79C Ball Type C\">RB-79 Mobile Pod Ball \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,000\n</td>\n<td>2004 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes two hangar personnel figurines.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>077 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/38/Mg-rms-099-qb.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206173138\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rms-099-qb\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rms-099-qb.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rms-099-qb.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/38/Mg-rms-099-qb.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206173138\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RMS-099_Rick_Dias\" title=\"RMS-099 Rick Dias\">RMS-099 Rick Dias (Quattro Vageena Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,600\n</td>\n<td>2004 December\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-070. Features parts to make different configurations for the rear skirt, backpack binders, and legs. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Quattro Bajeena</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-11. K runner is not bagged.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>078 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/af/Mg-rx-78-0079.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206173230\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78-0079\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78-0079.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78-0079.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/af/Mg-rx-78-0079.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206173230\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-2_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-2 Gundam\">RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.One Year War 0079</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_One_Year_War\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The One Year War\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The One Year War</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,200\n</td>\n<td>2005 March\n</td>\n<td>Uses the I and J plate runners of MG-028. Includes Gundam Hammer and <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine. Does not come with a Core Fighter unlike other MG RX-78-2 kits. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-4. First kit to include articulated hands with pegs and 3-finger parts that can be separated for additional articulation. Released to coincide with the release of PlayStation 2 game <i>Mobile Suit Gundam: The One Year War</i> and the 25th anniversary of Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>079 \u200e<figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/83/Mg-rb79k.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201150653\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rb79k\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rb79k.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rb79k.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/83/Mg-rb79k.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201150653\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RB-79K_Ball_Type_K\" title=\"RB-79K Ball Type K\">RB-79K Ball</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_08th_MS_Team\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,400\n</td>\n<td>2005 May\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-076. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-9.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>080 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bb/MG_-_MSM-04_-_Acguy_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110223193649\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - MSM-04 - Acguy - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - MSM-04 - Acguy - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_MSM-04_-_Acguy_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bb/MG_-_MSM-04_-_Acguy_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110223193649\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSM-04_Acguy\" title=\"MSM-04 Acguy\">MSM-04 Acguy</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2005 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes effect parts for torpedoes and foot propellers, stub piece to replicate missing right arm in <i>08th MS Team</i>, display base, and figurines of <a href=\"/wiki/Akahana\" title=\"Akahana\">Akahana</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Kikka_Kobayashi\" title=\"Kikka Kobayashi\">Kikka</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Katz_Kobayashi\" title=\"Katz Kobayashi\">Katz</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Letz_Kobayashi\" title=\"Letz Kobayashi\">Letz</a> and a Zeon diver. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-14.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>081 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9e/Mg-msn-001-ballute.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201152052\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msn-001-ballute\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msn-001-ballute.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msn-001-ballute.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9e/Mg-msn-001-ballute.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201152052\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-00100_Hyaku_Shiki\" title=\"MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki\">MSN-00100 Hyaku-Shiki + Ballute Pack</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2005 September\n</td>\n<td>Non-chrome plated variant of MG-037 with Ballute System.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>082 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/15/Mg-rx-178.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151104025820\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-178\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-178.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-178.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/15/Mg-rx-178.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151104025820\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-178_Gundam_Mk-II\" title=\"RX-178 Gundam Mk-II\">RX-178 Gundam Mk-II (A.E.U.G.) Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2005 October\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-014 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes custom launchpad, and figurines of <a href=\"/wiki/Kamille_Bidan\" title=\"Kamille Bidan\">Kamille Bidan</a> and two hangar personnel. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-19. First MG Ver.2.0. Released to commemorate the 20th anniversary of <i>Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</i> and the release of the theatrical compilation trilogy <i>A New Translation</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>083 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8f/MG_-_MSZ-006_-_Zeta_Gundam_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110223163849\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - MSZ-006 - Zeta Gundam - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - MSZ-006 - Zeta Gundam - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_MSZ-006_-_Zeta_Gundam_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8f/MG_-_MSZ-006_-_Zeta_Gundam_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110223163849\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-006_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam\">MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2005 December\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-005 with improved articulation and proportions. Fully transformable kit. Includes Hyper Mega Launcher, Grenade Launcher packs, <a href=\"/wiki/Fa_Yuiry\" title=\"Fa Yuiry\">Fa Yuiry</a> and hangar personnel figurines, and custom launchpad that links with MG-082's launchpad. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-20.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>084 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/88/MG_-_MSA-003_-_Nemo_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110223194100\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - MSA-003 - Nemo - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - MSA-003 - Nemo - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_MSA-003_-_Nemo_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/88/MG_-_MSA-003_-_Nemo_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110223194100\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSA-003_Nemo\" title=\"MSA-003 Nemo\">MSA-003 Nemo</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>2006 February\n</td>\n<td>Includes A.E.U.G. pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>085 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a2/Mg-rx-178t-ver2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151104030456\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-178t-ver2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"129\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-178t-ver2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-178t-ver2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a2/Mg-rx-178t-ver2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151104030456\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-178_Gundam_Mk-II\" title=\"RX-178 Gundam Mk-II\">RX-178 Gundam Mk-II (Titans) Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2006 March\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-082; redesign of MG-015 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes Titans pilot figurine. Launchpad display and hangar personnel figurines not included.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>086 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ae/YMS-15_Gyan_MG_boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20101114194702\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"YMS-15 Gyan MG boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"130\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"YMS-15 Gyan MG boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"YMS-15_Gyan_MG_boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ae/YMS-15_Gyan_MG_boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20101114194702\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/YMS-15_Gyan\" title=\"YMS-15 Gyan\">YMS-15 Gyan</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,600\n</td>\n<td>2006 May\n</td>\n<td>Features LED light-up beam saber (requires one CR1220 watch battery). Includes non-LED beam saber, three hide bombs, effect parts for Needle Missiles, and one 1/20 and two 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/M%27Quve\" title=\"M&#39;Quve\">M'Quve</a> figurines. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-26.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>087 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/da/MG_-_F91_Gundam_F91_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110223164226\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - F91 Gundam F91 - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - F91 Gundam F91 - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_F91_Gundam_F91_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/da/MG_-_F91_Gundam_F91_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110223164226\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/F91_Gundam_F91\" title=\"F91 Gundam F91\">F91 Gundam F91</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_F91\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam F91\">Mobile Suit Gundam F91</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,200\n</td>\n<td>2006 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Seabook_Arno\" title=\"Seabook Arno\">Seabook Arno</a> figurine, and <a href=\"/wiki/XMA-01_Rafflesia\" title=\"XMA-01 Rafflesia\">XMA-01 Rafflesia</a> display base with <a href=\"/wiki/Iron_Mask\" title=\"Iron Mask\">Iron Mask</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-25. First MG kit to not include any polycaps.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>088 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4b/Mg-rb-79sm.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202042506\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rb-79sm\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"161\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rb-79sm.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rb-79sm.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4b/Mg-rb-79sm.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202042506\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RB-79_Ball\" title=\"RB-79 Ball\">RB-79 Ball (Shark Mouth)</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_MS_IGLOO\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam MS IGLOO\">Mobile Suit Gundam MS IGLOO</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,200\n</td>\n<td>2006 August\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-076.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>089 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/fa/Mg-xm-x1.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120202041950\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-xm-x1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-xm-x1.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-xm-x1.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/fa/Mg-xm-x1.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120202041950\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XM-X1_Crossbone_Gundam_X-1\" title=\"XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1\">XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X1 \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Crossbone_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam\">Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2006 September\n</td>\n<td>Uses the F and G plate runners of MG-087. Includes transformable Core Fighter, Scissor Anchor, Anti Beam Coating Cloak, <a href=\"/wiki/Tobia_Arronax\" title=\"Tobia Arronax\">Tobia Arronax</a> figurine, an extra \"Skull Heart\" chest piece, and extra back skirt parts to create <a href=\"/wiki/XM-X1_Crossbone_Gundam_X-1_Kai\" title=\"XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 Kai\">XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X1 Kai</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/XM-X1_Crossbone_Gundam_X-1_Kai_Kai_%22Skull_Heart%22\" title=\"XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 Kai Kai &quot;Skull Heart&quot;\">X1 Kai Kai</a>. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-33.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>090 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ad/Strike-iwsp-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201145638\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Strike-iwsp-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Strike-iwsp-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Strike-iwsp-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ad/Strike-iwsp-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201145638\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105%2BP202QX_Strike_Gundam_IWSP\" title=\"GAT-X105+P202QX Strike Gundam IWSP\">GAT-X105 Strike Gundam + I.W.S.P.</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_MSV\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED MSV\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED MSV</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2006 October\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-065. Includes display base and <a href=\"/wiki/Sven_Cal_Bayang\" title=\"Sven Cal Bayang\">Sven Cal Bayang</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>091 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ec/Mg-f91-hm.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206093209\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-f91-hm\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-f91-hm.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-f91-hm.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ec/Mg-f91-hm.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206093209\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/F91_Gundam_F91\" title=\"F91 Gundam F91\">F91 Gundam F91 (Harrison Madin Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Crossbone_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam\">Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,000\n</td>\n<td>2006 November\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-087 with new right forearm armor; without Rafflesia display stand. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Harrison_Madin\" title=\"Harrison Madin\">Harrison Madin</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>092 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2f/Mg-rgm79-g-sniper.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201150012\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rgm79-g-sniper\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"129\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rgm79-g-sniper.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rgm79-g-sniper.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2f/Mg-rgm79-g-sniper.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201150012\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79%EF%BC%BBG%EF%BC%BD_GM_Sniper\" title=\"RGM-79\uff3bG\uff3d GM Sniper\">RGM-79\uff3bG\uff3d GM Sniper</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_08th_MS_Team\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2006 November\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-040. Includes camouflage net and Earth Federation pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>093 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e3/Mg-sf.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201151511\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-sf\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-sf.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-sf.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e3/Mg-sf.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201151511\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X20A_Strike_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2006 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes display base, and <a href=\"/wiki/Kira_Yamato\" title=\"Kira Yamato\">Kira Yamato</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Lacus_Clyne\" title=\"Lacus Clyne\">Lacus Clyne</a> figurines. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-31.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>094 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3a/Skullheart-fc-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120127165051\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Skullheart-fc-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Skullheart-fc-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Skullheart-fc-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3a/Skullheart-fc-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120127165051\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XM-X1_Crossbone_Gundam_X-1_Full_Cloth\" title=\"XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 Full Cloth\">XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 Full Cloth</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Crossbone_Gundam:_Steel_7\" title=\"Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam: Steel 7\">Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam: Steel 7</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2007 January\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-089.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>095 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5d/Hi-nu_gundam_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206174719\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Hi-nu gundam Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"54\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Hi-nu gundam Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Hi-nu_gundam_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5d/Hi-nu_gundam_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206174719\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-93-%CE%BD2_Hi-%CE%BD_Gundam\" title=\"RX-93-\u03bd2 Hi-\u03bd Gundam\">RX-93-\u03bd2 Hi-\u03bd Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack_-_Beltorchika%27s_Children\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack - Beltorchika&#39;s Children\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2007 February\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine, a custom display base in the form of his personal insignia, and effect parts for the Fin Funnels. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-32.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>096 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c8/Mg-strike-noir.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201152649\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-strike-noir\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-strike-noir.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-strike-noir.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c8/Mg-strike-noir.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201152649\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105E_Strike_Noir_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105E Strike Noir Gundam\">GAT-X105E Strike Noir Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_C.E._73:_STARGAZER\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED C.E. 73: STARGAZER\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED C.E. 73: STARGAZER</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2007 March\n</td>\n<td>Uses the D and F plate runners of MG-065. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Sven_Cal_Bayang\" title=\"Sven Cal Bayang\">Sven Cal Bayang</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-34.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>097 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/38/Mg-ms-06j-ver2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206173421\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-06j-ver2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-06j-ver2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-06j-ver2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/38/Mg-ms-06j-ver2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206173421\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06J_Zaku_II_Ground_Type\" title=\"MS-06J Zaku II Ground Type\">MS-06J Zaku II Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2007 April\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-003 with improved articulation and proportions. Features a gear mechanism that moves the monoeye when the head is turned sideways and a swivel mechanism that moves the cockpit left or right. Utilizes an assembly system for the cables where the individual rings slide through a rod or spring. Includes Missile Pods and Zeon pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-40/59.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>098 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/79/Mg-ms-06s-ver2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206173508\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-06s-ver2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-06s-ver2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-06s-ver2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/79/Mg-ms-06s-ver2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206173508\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06S_Zaku_II_Commander_Type\" title=\"MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type\">MS-06S Zaku II (Char Aznable Custom) Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2007 May\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-097; redesign of MG-002 with improved articulation and proportions. Missile Pods replaced by Lift unit. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-41.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>099 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/76/Mg-ms14s-ver2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201153454\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms14s-ver2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms14s-ver2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms14s-ver2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/76/Mg-ms14s-ver2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201153454\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-14S_Gelgoog_Commander_Type\" title=\"MS-14S Gelgoog Commander Type\">MS-14S Gelgoog (Char Aznable Custom) Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2007 July\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-008 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes a 1/100 scale electric car, and figurines of <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Lalah_Sun\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lalah Sun\">Lalah Sun</a> to replicate a scene from <a href=\"/wiki/Char_and_Sayla\" title=\"Char and Sayla\">episode 37</a>. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-41.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>100 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/20/MG_Turn_A_Gundam_regular_boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20230908162646\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Turn A Gundam regular boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Turn A Gundam regular boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Turn_A_Gundam_regular_boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/20/MG_Turn_A_Gundam_regular_boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20230908162646\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/System-%E2%88%8099_%E2%88%80_Gundam\" title=\"System-\u220099 \u2200 Gundam\">WD-M01 \u2200 Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/%E2%88%80_Gundam\" title=\"\u2200 Gundam\">\u2200 Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2007 August\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Rolan_Cehack\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rolan Cehack\">Rolan Cehack</a> figurine, transformable Core Fighter, and a cow figurine to replicate scenes from the anime. \"Moonlight Butterfly\" effect parts are sold separately with P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit. First MG kit from the <a href=\"/wiki/Correct_Century\" title=\"Correct Century\">Correct Century</a> timeline. Selected by poll to be the 100th MG released. First MG kit to have stencilled letters on the runners rather than embossed to aid identification.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>101 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/11/MG_Destiny_SP_01.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20250307052710\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Destiny SP 01\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Destiny SP 01.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Destiny_SP_01.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/11/MG_Destiny_SP_01.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20250307052710\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X42S_Destiny_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X42S Destiny Gundam\">ZGMF-X42S Destiny Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2007 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes display base and <a href=\"/wiki/Shinn_Asuka\" title=\"Shinn Asuka\">Shinn Asuka</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Stella_Loussier\" title=\"Stella Loussier\">Stella Loussier</a> figurines. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-43.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>102 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e9/Mg-rx-0-ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206102017\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-0-ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"123\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-0-ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-0-ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e9/Mg-rx-0-ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206102017\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn_(Novel)\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn (Novel)\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i> (Novel)\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2007 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Banagher_Links\" title=\"Banagher Links\">Banagher Links</a> figurine. Beam Gatling Gun and Armed Armor DE were sold separately. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-44. Discontinued following the release of MG-131, but reissued in March 2018 alongside the release of MG-201. Reissues include renewed F plate runners introduced in MG-131 that improve knee articulation.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>103 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/MG_-_MS-06R-1A_-_Zaku_II_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110303080906\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - MS-06R-1A - Zaku II - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - MS-06R-1A - Zaku II - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_MS-06R-1A_-_Zaku_II_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/MG_-_MS-06R-1A_-_Zaku_II_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110303080906\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06R-1A_Zaku_II_High_Mobility_Type\" title=\"MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type\">MS-06R-1A Zaku II (Black Tri-Stars) Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 January\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-097; redesign of MG-020 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Tri-Stars\" title=\"Black Tri-Stars\">Black Tri-Stars</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-45.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>104 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/db/Mg-strike-iswp-lk.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206102559\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-strike-iswp-lk\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-strike-iswp-lk.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-strike-iswp-lk.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/db/Mg-strike-iswp-lk.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206102559\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105E%2BAQM/E-M1_Strike_Gundam_E_IWSP\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"GAT-X105E+AQM/E-M1 Strike Gundam E IWSP\">GAT-X105E Lukas's Strike E + I.W.S.P.</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Frame_Astrays\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Frame Astrays\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Frame Astrays</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-096 with the Noir Striker replaced by the IWSP unit from MG-090. Includes display base and <a href=\"/wiki/Lukas_O%27Donnell\" title=\"Lukas O&#39;Donnell\">Lukas O'Donnell</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>105 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d0/MG_Zaku_Minelayer.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120211091756\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Zaku Minelayer\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Zaku Minelayer.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Zaku_Minelayer.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d0/MG_Zaku_Minelayer.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120211091756\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06F_Zaku_Minelayer\" title=\"MS-06F Zaku Minelayer\">MS-06F Zaku Minelayer</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-097. Includes Minelayer Backpack. Missile Pods replaced by Mine Pods.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>106 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/17/Mg-ms06-f.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206102836\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms06-f\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms06-f.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms06-f.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/17/Mg-ms06-f.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206102836\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06F_Zaku_II\" title=\"MS-06F Zaku II\">MS-06F Zaku II Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-097. Includes parts to convert Zaku Bazooka into Giant Bazooka, and a colony hatch dial piece for <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_1\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 1</a> to replicate scene from <a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Rising\" title=\"Gundam Rising\">episode 1</a> of the TV series.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>107 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/52/MG_-_MS-14A_-_Gelgoog_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110223193333\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - MS-14A - Gelgoog - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - MS-14A - Gelgoog - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_MS-14A_-_Gelgoog_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/52/MG_-_MS-14A_-_Gelgoog_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110223193333\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-14A_Gelgoog\" title=\"MS-14A Gelgoog\">MS-14A Gelgoog Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 April\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-099. Includes Zeon pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>108 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ae/Mg-launcher-strike.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206103101\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-launcher-strike\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-launcher-strike.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-launcher-strike.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ae/Mg-launcher-strike.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206103101\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td>GAT-X105 <a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105%2BAQM/E-X03_Launcher_Strike_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105+AQM/E-X03 Launcher Strike Gundam\">Launcher</a>/<a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105%2BAQM/E-X02_Sword_Strike_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105+AQM/E-X02 Sword Strike Gundam\">Sword</a> Strike Gundam\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2008 April\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-065. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-49.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>109 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/Mg-force-impulse.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206103307\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-force-impulse\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-force-impulse.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-force-impulse.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/Mg-force-impulse.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206103307\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X56S/%CE%B1_Force_Impulse_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X56S/\u03b1 Force Impulse Gundam\">ZGMF-X56S/\u03b1 Force Impulse Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 May\n</td>\n<td>Includes Silhouette Flyer, figurines of <a href=\"/wiki/Shinn_Asuka\" title=\"Shinn Asuka\">Shinn Asuka</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Lunamaria_Hawke\" title=\"Lunamaria Hawke\">Lunamaria Hawke</a>, connector piece which allows compatibility with MG <a href=\"/wiki/Striker_Packs\" title=\"Striker Packs\">Striker Packs</a>, and a part of Sword Impulse's Excalibur to replicate a scene from <a href=\"/wiki/Nightmare\" title=\"Nightmare\">episode 34</a>. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-50. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>110 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c9/Shin_Musha_GundamX.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206112622\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Shin Musha GundamX\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Shin Musha GundamX.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Shin_Musha_GundamX.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c9/Shin_Musha_GundamX.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206112622\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Musha_Gundam\" title=\"Musha Gundam\">Shin Musha Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Plamo-Kyoshiro\" title=\"Plamo-Kyoshiro\">Plamo-Kyoshiro</a></i> / <a href=\"/wiki/Dynasty_Warriors_Gundam_2\" title=\"Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2\">Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2008 June\n</td>\n<td>Uses frame from MG-028 and the body of MG-078. From the '<b><a href=\"/wiki/Plamo-Kyoshiro\" title=\"Plamo-Kyoshiro\">Plamo-Kyoshiro</a>'</b> series but with the design based on its appearance on <i><a href=\"/wiki/Dynasty_Warriors_Gundam_2\" title=\"Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2\">Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2</a></i>. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-51. China/Hong Kong release includes a set of flower decals.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>111 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b6/Mg-rx-78-2-ver2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206173558\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-78-2-ver2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-78-2-ver2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-78-2-ver2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b6/Mg-rx-78-2-ver2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206173558\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-2_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-2 Gundam\">RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2008 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes two <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurines and a clear display stand for <a href=\"/wiki/FF-X7_Core_Fighter\" title=\"FF-X7 Core Fighter\">FF-X7 Core Fighter</a>. Reuses Gundam Hammer from MG-100. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-52/60. Released to commemorate the 30th anniversary of <i>Gundam</i>, this kit is designed to closely resemble the anime line art.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>112 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bf/Mg-ms-06k.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206103411\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-06k\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-06k.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-06k.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bf/Mg-ms-06k.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206103411\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06K_Zaku_Cannon\" title=\"MS-06K Zaku Cannon\">MS-06K Zakucannon</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 August\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-097. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-58.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>113 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c5/Ms-06r2-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120127134415\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Ms-06r2-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Ms-06r2-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Ms-06r2-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c5/Ms-06r2-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120127134415\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06R-2_Zaku_II_High_Mobility_Type\" title=\"MS-06R-2 Zaku II High Mobility Type\">MS-06R-2 Zaku II (Johnny Ridden Custom) Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 September\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-103; redesign of MG-007 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Johnny_Ridden\" title=\"Johnny Ridden\">Johnny Ridden</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-56.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>114 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/84/Infinite-justice-mg-art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120211091917\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Infinite-justice-mg-art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Infinite-justice-mg-art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Infinite-justice-mg-art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/84/Infinite-justice-mg-art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120211091917\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X19A_%E2%88%9E_Justice_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X19A \u221e Justice Gundam\">ZGMF-X19A \u221e Justice Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2008 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Athrun_Zala\" title=\"Athrun Zala\">Athrun Zala</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-5.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>115 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/47/Ms-06r1a-mg-shin.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110919190811\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Ms-06r1a-mg-shin\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Ms-06r1a-mg-shin.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Ms-06r1a-mg-shin.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/47/Ms-06r1a-mg-shin.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110919190811\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06R-1A_Zaku_II_High_Mobility_Type\" title=\"MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type\">MS-06R-1A Zaku II (Shin Matsunaga Custom) Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2008 November\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-103; redesign of MG-006 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Shin_Matsunaga\" title=\"Shin Matsunaga\">Shin Matsunaga</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-56.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>116 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/35/Mg-msn-06-ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151113020907\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-msn-06-ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-msn-06-ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-msn-06-ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/35/Mg-msn-06-ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151113020907\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-06S_Sinanju\" title=\"MSN-06S Sinanju\">MSN-06S Sinanju \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn_(Novel)\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn (Novel)\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i> (Novel)\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2008 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Full_Frontal\" title=\"Full Frontal\">Full Frontal</a> figurine and water slide decal sheet. Rocket Bazooka was sold separately; water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-57.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>117 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ec/MG_G-Fighter_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20251106030400\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG G-Fighter Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG G-Fighter Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_G-Fighter_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ec/MG_G-Fighter_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20251106030400\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/G-Fighter\" title=\"G-Fighter\">G Fighter</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,600\n</td>\n<td>2009 January\n</td>\n<td>Accessory kit for MG-111. Includes Hyper Hammer and figurines of <a href=\"/wiki/Sayla_Mass\" title=\"Sayla Mass\">Sayla Mass</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Sleggar_Law\" title=\"Sleggar Law\">Sleggar Law</a>, and two hangar crew members. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-62.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>118 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/96/Mg-rgm-79-ver2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206104025\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rgm-79-ver2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rgm-79-ver2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rgm-79-ver2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/96/Mg-rgm-79-ver2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206104025\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79_GM\" title=\"RGM-79 GM\">RGM-79 GM Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2009 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-111; redesign of MG-017 with improved articulation and proportions. Features the option to use two-piece or three-piece front skirt armor. Includes removable cockpit block and Earth Federation pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-61. Like MG-111, this kit is designed to closely resemble the anime line art and shares the same inner frame and weapon parts.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>119 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f8/Sword-impulse-morishita.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120201180613\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Sword-impulse-morishita\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Sword-impulse-morishita.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Sword-impulse-morishita.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f8/Sword-impulse-morishita.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120201180613\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X56S/%CE%B2_Sword_Impulse_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X56S/\u03b2 Sword Impulse Gundam\">ZGMF-X56S/\u03b2 Sword Impulse Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2009 April\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-109. Includes two non-articulated hands to hold the Excaliburs. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-67.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>120 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/ff/Mg-ms-07-ver2.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206104243\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-07-ver2\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-07-ver2.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-07-ver2.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/ff/Mg-ms-07-ver2.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206104243\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-07B_Gouf\" title=\"MS-07B Gouf\">MS-07B Gouf Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2009 May\n</td>\n<td>Uses the G and H plate runners of MG-097; redesign of MG-032 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Ramba_Ral\" title=\"Ramba Ral\">Ramba Ral</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Crowley_Hamon\" title=\"Crowley Hamon\">Crowley Hamon</a> figurines. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-68.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>121 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1c/Mg-g-armor-rt.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206110316\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-g-armor-rt\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"55\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-g-armor-rt.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-g-armor-rt.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1c/Mg-g-armor-rt.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206110316\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/G-Armor\" title=\"G-Armor\">G-Armor Realtype Color</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a59,800\n</td>\n<td>2009 June\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-111 and MG-117. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-70.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>122 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/73/Mg-ms-06j-white-ogre.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120216071217\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ms-06j-white-ogre\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ms-06j-white-ogre.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ms-06j-white-ogre.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/73/Mg-ms-06j-white-ogre.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120216071217\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06J_Zaku_II_Ground_Type\" title=\"MS-06J Zaku II Ground Type\">MS-06J Zaku II \"White Ogre\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_MS_IGLOO_2:_The_Gravity_Front\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam MS IGLOO 2: The Gravity Front\">Mobile Suit Gundam MS IGLOO 2: The Gravity Front</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2009 June\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-097. Includes Zaku Bazooka ammo packs.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>123 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c6/MG_-_GN-001_-_Gundam_Exia_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110223164735\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG - GN-001 - Gundam Exia - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG - GN-001 - Gundam Exia - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_-_GN-001_-_Gundam_Exia_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c6/MG_-_GN-001_-_Gundam_Exia_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110223164735\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GN-001_Gundam_Exia\" title=\"GN-001 Gundam Exia\">GN-001 Gundam Exia</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2009 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Setsuna_F._Seiei\" title=\"Setsuna F. Seiei\">Setsuna F. Seiei</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Karel\" title=\"Karel\">Karel</a> figurines, and a display base for the <a href=\"/wiki/GN_Drive\" title=\"GN Drive\">GN Drive</a>. GN Drive accommodates two Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-69. First MG kit from the <a href=\"/wiki/Anno_Domini\" title=\"Anno Domini\">Anno Domini</a> timeline.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>124 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a5/Mg-rx-75.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206110703\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-rx-75\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-rx-75.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-rx-75.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a5/Mg-rx-75.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206110703\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-75-4_Guntank\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RX-75-4 Guntank\">RX-75-4 Guntank</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2009 September\n</td>\n<td>Features movable missile launcher tubes when the forearms are rotated. Includes one Gunpla LED Unit Green, transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FF-X7_Core_Fighter\" title=\"FF-X7 Core Fighter\">FF-X7 Core Fighter</a>, and figurines of <a href=\"/wiki/Hayato_Kobayashi\" title=\"Hayato Kobayashi\">Hayato Kobayashi</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Ryu_Jose\" title=\"Ryu Jose\">Ryu Jose</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Bright_Noa\" title=\"Bright Noa\">Bright Noa</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Mirai_Noa\" title=\"Mirai Noa\">Mirai Yashima</a>. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-73.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>125 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/44/Mg-blue-frame.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206110947\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-blue-frame\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-blue-frame.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-blue-frame.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/44/Mg-blue-frame.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206110947\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MBF-P03R_Gundam_Astray_Blue_Frame_2nd_Revise\" title=\"MBF-P03R Gundam Astray Blue Frame 2nd Revise\">MBF-P03R Gundam Astray Blue Frame Second Revise</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_VS_Astray\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2009 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Gai_Murakumo\" title=\"Gai Murakumo\">Gai Murakumo</a> figurine and blue <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_2\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 2</a> with adapter for the Tactical Arms II. Initial releases included an extra runner with adapter parts to fit Striker Packs from the <a href=\"/wiki/1/100_Gundam_SEED_Model_Series\" title=\"1/100 Gundam SEED Model Series\">1/100 Gundam SEED Model Series</a>. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-74.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>126 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b9/Mg-amx-004mkii-ple.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151203030502\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-amx-004mkii-ple\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-amx-004mkii-ple.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-amx-004mkii-ple.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b9/Mg-amx-004mkii-ple.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151203030502\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AMX-004_Qubeley_Mk-II\" title=\"AMX-004 Qubeley Mk-II\">AMX-004-2 Qubeley Mk-II (Elpeo Ple Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_ZZ\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ\">Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2009 November\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-041. Includes 1/20 and 1/100 scale <a href=\"/wiki/Elpeo_Ple\" title=\"Elpeo Ple\">Elpeo Ple</a> figures and custom decals designed by Pepper Shop.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>127 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/87/Mg-vgundam-ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206111810\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-vgundam-ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-vgundam-ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-vgundam-ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/87/Mg-vgundam-ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206111810\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/LM312V04_Victory_Gundam\" title=\"LM312V04 Victory Gundam\">LM312V04/06 Victory Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Victory_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Victory Gundam\">Mobile Suit Victory Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2009 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/%C3%9Cso_Ewin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"\u00dcso Ewin\">\u00dcso Ewin</a> (standing and sitting) and <a href=\"/wiki/Marbet_Fingerhat\" title=\"Marbet Fingerhat\">Marbet Fingerhat</a> (sitting) figurine and an extra Core Fighter ( to create <a href=\"/wiki/LM312V06_Victory_Gundam_Hexa\" title=\"LM312V06 Victory Gundam Hexa\">LM312V06 Victory Gundam Hexa</a>. Also includes an extra PE-molded V-fin as a callback to most <a href=\"/wiki/1/100_High_Grade_Victory_Gundam_Model_Series\" title=\"1/100 High Grade Victory Gundam Model Series\">HGVG</a> kits. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-75. Fully transformable kit. First MG kit to use swappable fingers for hands with an articulated thumb, which would become the standard for MG kits that do not use Emotion Manipulator SP plate runner.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>128 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a1/0161537.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20130414065332\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"0161537\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"0161537.jpg\" data-image-key=\"0161537.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a1/0161537.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20130414065332\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-3_G-3_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-3 G-3 Gundam\">RX-78-3 Gundam Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2009 December\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-111; redesign of MG-004 with improved articulation and proportions.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>129 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/43/MG_GN-X.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110116232324\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG GN-X\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"152\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG GN-X.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_GN-X.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/43/MG_GN-X.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110116232324\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GNX-603T_GN-X\" title=\"GNX-603T GN-X\">GNX-603T GN-X</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,600\n</td>\n<td>2010 January\n</td>\n<td>Uses the F and H plate runners of MG-123. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Soma_Peries\" title=\"Soma Peries\">Soma Peries</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Sergei_Smirnov\" title=\"Sergei Smirnov\">Sergei Smirnov</a> figurines and a display base for the <a href=\"/wiki/GN_Drive_Tau\" title=\"GN Drive Tau\">GN Drive Tau</a> unit. GN Drive Tau accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-80.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>130 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/19/MG_Gundam_Astray_Red_Frame_Kai.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180829184407\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam Astray Red Frame Kai\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam Astray Red Frame Kai.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_Astray_Red_Frame_Kai.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/19/MG_Gundam_Astray_Red_Frame_Kai.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180829184407\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MBF-P02Kai_Gundam_Astray_Red_Frame_Kai\" title=\"MBF-P02Kai Gundam Astray Red Frame Kai\">MBF-P02Kai Gundam Astray Red Frame</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_VS_Astray\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2010 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-125. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Lowe_Guele\" title=\"Lowe Guele\">Lowe Guele</a> figurine and red <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_2\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 2</a> with adapter for the Tactical Arms IIL.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>131 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/06/Rx-0-mgboxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151201113512\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Rx-0-mgboxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Rx-0-mgboxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Rx-0-mgboxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/06/Rx-0-mgboxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151201113512\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam (OVA Ver.)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2010 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-102 with R1 and R2 plate runners for improved knee and waist articulation, plus a new head sculpt. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Banagher_Links\" title=\"Banagher Links\">Banagher Links</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>132 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/47/Mg_wing_tv.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120210162135\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg wing tv\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg wing tv.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_wing_tv.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/47/Mg_wing_tv.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120210162135\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01W_Wing_Gundam\" title=\"XXXG-01W Wing Gundam\">XXXG-01W Wing Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Wing\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Wing\">Mobile Suit Gundam Wing</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2010 April\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Heero_Yuy\" title=\"Heero Yuy\">Heero Yuy</a> (in <a href=\"/wiki/The_Shooting_Star_She_Saw\" title=\"The Shooting Star She Saw\">episode 1</a> school uniform) figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-81. Released to commemorate the 15th anniversary of <i>Gundam Wing</i>. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>133 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ea/Mush_Gundam_Mk._II_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20101109040231\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mush Gundam Mk. II Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mush Gundam Mk. II Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mush_Gundam_Mk._II_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ea/Mush_Gundam_Mk._II_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20101109040231\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Musha_Gundam_Mk._II\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Musha Gundam Mk. II\">Musha Gundam Mk-II</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Dynasty_Warriors_Gundam_2\" title=\"Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2\">Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2010 May\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-082. Features gold chrome plated parts. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-82. China/Hong Kong release includes a set of flower decals.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>134 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e6/MG_FA_78-1_Gundam.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20101112083302\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG FA 78-1 Gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG FA 78-1 Gundam.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_FA_78-1_Gundam.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e6/MG_FA_78-1_Gundam.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20101112083302\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/FA-78-1_Full_Armor_Gundam\" title=\"FA-78-1 Full Armor Gundam\">FA-78-1 Full Armor Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2010 June\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-111 with additional armor parts, which attach to the kit using double-sided tapes. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-83.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>135 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3c/LM312V04SD-VB03A-corebooster-verka-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120113121844\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"LM312V04SD-VB03A-corebooster-verka-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"64\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"LM312V04SD-VB03A-corebooster-verka-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"LM312V04SD-VB03A-corebooster-verka-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3c/LM312V04SD-VB03A-corebooster-verka-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120113121844\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/LM312V04%2BSD-VB03A_V-Dash_Gundam\" title=\"LM312V04+SD-VB03A V-Dash Gundam\">LM312V04(B-part)+SD-VB03A Core Booster \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Victory_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Victory Gundam\">Mobile Suit Victory Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,200\n</td>\n<td>2010 July\n</td>\n<td>Accessory kit for MG-127. Contains two Core Fighters: one for <a href=\"/wiki/LM312V04_Victory_Gundam\" title=\"LM312V04 Victory Gundam\">Victory Gundam</a> and one for <a href=\"/wiki/LM312V06_Victory_Gundam_Hexa\" title=\"LM312V06 Victory Gundam Hexa\">Victory Gundam Hexa</a>. Includes additional weapons and black BA-1 display base.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>136 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/LM312V04SD-VB03A-verka-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120113121811\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"LM312V04SD-VB03A-verka-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"LM312V04SD-VB03A-verka-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"LM312V04SD-VB03A-verka-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/LM312V04SD-VB03A-verka-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120113121811\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/LM312V04%2BSD-VB03A_V-Dash_Gundam\" title=\"LM312V04+SD-VB03A V-Dash Gundam\">LM312V04+SD-VB03A V-Dash Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Victory_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Victory Gundam\">Mobile Suit Victory Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,800\n</td>\n<td>2010 July\n</td>\n<td>Re-release of MG-127 with parts from MG-135.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>137 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/74/MG_The_O_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20250307053047\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG The O Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"59\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG The O Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_The_O_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/74/MG_The_O_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20250307053047\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/PMX-003_The-O\" title=\"PMX-003 The-O\">PMX-003 The-O</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a512,000\n</td>\n<td>2010 August\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Paptimus_Scirocco\" title=\"Paptimus Scirocco\">Paptimus Scirocco</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-90. Released to commemorate the 25th anniversary of <i>Zeta Gundam</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>138 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/42/Mg-deathscythe-ew.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120113115132\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-deathscythe-ew\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"157\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-deathscythe-ew.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-deathscythe-ew.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/42/Mg-deathscythe-ew.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120113115132\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01D_Gundam_Deathscythe_EW\" title=\"XXXG-01D Gundam Deathscythe EW\">XXXG-01D Gundam Deathscythe</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2010 September\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Duo_Maxwell\" title=\"Duo Maxwell\">Duo Maxwell</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-88.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>139 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4c/Rezel-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20100926103741\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Rezel-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Rezel-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Rezel-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4c/Rezel-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20100926103741\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGZ-95_ReZEL\" title=\"RGZ-95 ReZEL\">RGZ-95 ReZEL</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2010 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes two <a href=\"/wiki/Riddhe_Marcenas\" title=\"Riddhe Marcenas\">Riddhe Marcenas</a> figurines and <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_1\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 1</a> adapter for Wave Rider mode. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>140 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d4/MG_QanT.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20101101215543\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG QanT\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG QanT.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_QanT.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d4/MG_QanT.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20101101215543\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GNT-0000_00_Qan%EF%BC%BBT%EF%BC%BD\" title=\"GNT-0000 00 Qan\uff3bT\uff3d\">GNT-0000 00 Qan[T]</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00_The_Movie_-A_wakening_of_the_Trailblazer-\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00 The Movie -A wakening of the Trailblazer-\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00 The Movie -A wakening of the Trailblazer-</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2010 November\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Setsuna_F._Seiei\" title=\"Setsuna F. Seiei\">Setsuna F. Seiei</a> figurine and black <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_2\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 2</a> for GN Sword V in Buster Rifle mode. Chest accommodates two Gunpla LED Units (sold separately). Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-89. As an undocumented feature, armor parts can be removed and GN Condensers in the arms and legs can be extended to recreate Quantum Burst mode.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>141 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c0/Rgz-95c-mg.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20111226132403\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Rgz-95c-mg\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Rgz-95c-mg.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Rgz-95c-mg.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c0/Rgz-95c-mg.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20111226132403\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGZ-95C_ReZEL_Commander_Type\" title=\"RGZ-95C ReZEL Commander Type\">RGZ-95C ReZEL Commander Type</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2011 January\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-139. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Norm_Basilicock\" title=\"Norm Basilicock\">Norm Basilicock</a> figurine. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>142 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4a/Deathscythe_h_boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110131151710\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Deathscythe h boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Deathscythe h boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Deathscythe_h_boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4a/Deathscythe_h_boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110131151710\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01D2_Gundam_Deathscythe_Hell_EW\" title=\"XXXG-01D2 Gundam Deathscythe Hell EW\">XXXG-01D2 Gundam Deathscythe Hell</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing:_Endless_Waltz\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2011 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-138.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>143 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/91/1-100_MG_Shenlong_Gundam_EW_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110225124550\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"1-100 MG Shenlong Gundam EW Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"1-100 MG Shenlong Gundam EW Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"1-100_MG_Shenlong_Gundam_EW_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/91/1-100_MG_Shenlong_Gundam_EW_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110225124550\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01S_Shenlong_Gundam_EW\" title=\"XXXG-01S Shenlong Gundam EW\">XXXG-01S Shenlong Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2011 March\n</td>\n<td>Uses the XA and XB plate runners of MG-138. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Chang_Wufei\" title=\"Chang Wufei\">Chang Wufei</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-92.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>144 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/93/Mg_wing_ew.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120113115426\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg wing ew\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg wing ew.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_wing_ew.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/93/Mg_wing_ew.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120113115426\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01W_Wing_Gundam_EW\" title=\"XXXG-01W Wing Gundam EW\">XXXG-01W Wing Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2011 March\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-069. Includes a custom mount part for <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_1\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 1</a>. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>145 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/MG_1-100_00_Raiser_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120107051530\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG 1-100 00 Raiser - Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG 1-100 00 Raiser - Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_1-100_00_Raiser_-_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/MG_1-100_00_Raiser_-_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120107051530\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GN-0000%2BGNR-010_00_Raiser\" title=\"GN-0000+GNR-010 00 Raiser\">GN-0000+GNR-010 00 Raiser</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,500\n</td>\n<td>2011 May\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Setsuna_F._Seiei\" title=\"Setsuna F. Seiei\">Setsuna F. Seiei</a> (civilian outfit) and <a href=\"/wiki/Saji_Crossroad\" title=\"Saji Crossroad\">Saji Crossroad</a> figurines, one Gunpla LED Unit Green, and GN Condensers to create <a href=\"/wiki/GN-0000RE%2BGNR-010_00_Raiser_GN_Condenser_Type\" title=\"GN-0000RE+GNR-010 00 Raiser GN Condenser Type\">GN-0000RE+GNR-010 00 Raiser GN Condenser Type</a>. Chest, GN Drives/Condensers, and O Raiser binders accommodate five Gunpla LED Units (sold separately). Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>146 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a3/Mg-epyon.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20121002135322\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-epyon\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-epyon.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-epyon.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a3/Mg-epyon.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20121002135322\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/OZ-13MS_Gundam_Epyon\" title=\"OZ-13MS Gundam Epyon\">OZ-13MS Gundam Epyon</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2011 June\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Zeches_Merquise\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Zeches Merquise\">Milliardo Peacecraft</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-98. First official Katoki redesign of the Gundam Epyon. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>147 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d2/Mg_delta_plus_boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151104070223\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg delta plus boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg delta plus boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_delta_plus_boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d2/Mg_delta_plus_boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151104070223\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-001A1_Delta_Plus\" title=\"MSN-001A1 Delta Plus\">MSN-001A1 Delta Plus</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2011 August\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Riddhe_Marcenas\" title=\"Riddhe Marcenas\">Riddhe Marcenas</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Mineva_Lao_Zabi\" title=\"Mineva Lao Zabi\">Audrey Burne</a> figurines, and additional parts to support the frame in Wave Rider mode. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>148 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b4/MG_1_100_GN-0000GNHW7SG.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20110830150202\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG 1 100 GN-0000GNHW7SG\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG 1 100 GN-0000GNHW7SG.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_1_100_GN-0000GNHW7SG.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b4/MG_1_100_GN-0000GNHW7SG.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110830150202\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GN-0000GNHW/7SG_00_Gundam_Seven_Sword/G\" title=\"GN-0000GNHW/7SG 00 Gundam Seven Sword/G\">GN-0000GNHW/7SG 00 Gundam Seven Sword/G</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00V:_Battlefield_Record\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00V: Battlefield Record\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00V: Battlefield Record</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,500\n</td>\n<td>2011 September\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-145. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Setsuna_F._Seiei\" title=\"Setsuna F. Seiei\">Setsuna F. Seiei</a> (civilian outfit) figurine and original parts to combine the two GN Katars into arm-mounted or handheld twin edge weapon. Chest, GN Drives, and GN Buster Sword II accommodate a total of four Gunpla LED Units (sold separately).\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>149 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8e/Mg-sandrock.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120206112024\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-sandrock\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-sandrock.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-sandrock.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8e/Mg-sandrock.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120206112024\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01SR_Gundam_Sandrock_EW\" title=\"XXXG-01SR Gundam Sandrock EW\">XXXG-01SR Gundam Sandrock</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2011 October\n</td>\n<td>Uses the XA and XB plate runners of MG-138. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Quatre_Raberba_Winner\" title=\"Quatre Raberba Winner\">Quatre Raberba Winner</a> figurine, Heat Shotel and Beam Machine Gun. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-99.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>150 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/34/Mg-full-armor-rx0-verka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120113115850\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-full-armor-rx0-verka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-full-armor-rx0-verka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-full-armor-rx0-verka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/34/Mg-full-armor-rx0-verka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120113115850\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Full_Armor_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Full Armor Unicorn Gundam\">RX-0 Full Armor Unicorn Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a58,000\n</td>\n<td>2011 December\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-102 with green Psycho-Frame and Y plate runner for improved knee articulation and leg hardpoints for Grenade racks. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Banagher_Links\" title=\"Banagher Links\">Banagher Links</a> figurine, two MG-exclusive Hyper Beam Javelin, and parts to create <a href=\"/wiki/Base_Jabber\" title=\"Base Jabber\">Type 94 Base Jabber</a> (includes two Earth Federation pilot figurines) for normal Unicorn Gundam. Armed Armor DE was sold separately.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>151 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7b/Mg-ew-heavyarms.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120113113222\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-ew-heavyarms\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-ew-heavyarms.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-ew-heavyarms.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/7b/Mg-ew-heavyarms.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120113113222\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01H_Gundam_Heavyarms\" title=\"XXXG-01H Gundam Heavyarms\">XXXG-01H Gundam Heavyarms EW</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2012 January\n</td>\n<td>Uses the XA and XB plate runners of MG-138. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Trowa_Barton\" title=\"Trowa Barton\">Trowa Barton</a> figurine, optional shield piece for Gatling Gun and hidden Beam Saber. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-100.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>152 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0b/MG_Duel_Gundam_Assaultshroud.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120211171717\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Duel Gundam Assaultshroud\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Duel Gundam Assaultshroud.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Duel_Gundam_Assaultshroud.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0b/MG_Duel_Gundam_Assaultshroud.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120211171717\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X102_Duel_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X102 Duel Gundam\">GAT-X102 Duel Gundam Assault Shroud</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2012 February\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Yzak_Jule\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Yzak Jule\">Yzak Jule</a> figurine and Bazooka that was not seen in the TV series. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately with MG <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X13A_Providence_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a> G.U.N.D.A.M. Edition. Released in conjunction with <i>Gundam SEED</i> Remaster project.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>153 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8d/MG_Age1.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120215085139\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Age1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"154\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Age1.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Age1.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8d/MG_Age1.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120215085139\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AGE-1_Gundam_AGE-1_Normal\" title=\"AGE-1 Gundam AGE-1 Normal\">Gundam AGE-1 Normal</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_AGE\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam AGE\">Mobile Suit Gundam AGE</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2012 February\n</td>\n<td>Features a specialized Inner Frame system. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Flit_Asuno\" title=\"Flit Asuno\">Flit Asuno</a> figurine and parts to create <a href=\"/wiki/AGE-1F_Gundam_AGE-1_Flat\" title=\"AGE-1F Gundam AGE-1 Flat\">AGE-1F Gundam AGE-1 Flat</a>. First MG kit from the <a href=\"/wiki/Advanced_Generation\" title=\"Advanced Generation\">Advanced Generation</a> timeline.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>154 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/Mg_age-1_titus.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120301043748\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg age-1 titus\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg age-1 titus.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_age-1_titus.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/Mg_age-1_titus.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120301043748\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AGE-1T_Gundam_AGE-1_Titus\" title=\"AGE-1T Gundam AGE-1 Titus\">Gundam AGE-1 Titus</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_AGE\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam AGE\">Mobile Suit Gundam AGE</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2012 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-153.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>155 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c6/Mg_rx-0_unicorn_gundam_02_banshee_boxart_large.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120512113508\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg rx-0 unicorn gundam 02 banshee boxart large\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg rx-0 unicorn gundam 02 banshee boxart large.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_rx-0_unicorn_gundam_02_banshee_boxart_large.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c6/Mg_rx-0_unicorn_gundam_02_banshee_boxart_large.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120512113508\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam_02_Banshee\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,500\n</td>\n<td>2012 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-102 with yellow Psycho-Frame; F plate runners are renewed for improved knee articulation. Includes articulated Armed Armor VN/BS and <a href=\"/wiki/Marida_Cruz\" title=\"Marida Cruz\">Marida Cruz</a> figurine, as well as a leftover <a href=\"/wiki/Banagher_Links\" title=\"Banagher Links\">Banagher Links</a> figurine from MG-102. Released to coincide with release of the 5th episode of the OVA.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>156 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b2/Mg-spallow-box.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120404102338\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-spallow-box\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-spallow-box.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-spallow-box.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b2/Mg-spallow-box.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120404102338\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AGE-1S_Gundam_AGE-1_Spallow\" title=\"AGE-1S Gundam AGE-1 Spallow\">Gundam AGE-1 Spallow</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_AGE\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam AGE\">Mobile Suit Gundam AGE</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2012 April\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-153.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>157 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2c/Marasai_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120502140753\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Marasai Box Art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Marasai Box Art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Marasai_Box_Art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2c/Marasai_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120502140753\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RMS-108_Marasai\" title=\"RMS-108 Marasai\">RMS-108 Marasai</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2012 May\n</td>\n<td>Includes Titans pilot figurine, \"round forming joint\" custom attachment for <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_1\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 1</a>, and adapter parts for the optional Ballute System. Upper torso accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately).\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>158 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ee/Mg_blitz_boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120605133242\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg blitz boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg blitz boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_blitz_boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ee/Mg_blitz_boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120605133242\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X207_Blitz_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X207 Blitz Gundam\">GAT-X207 Blitz Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2012 June\n</td>\n<td>Uses the B, C, D, E, and F plate runners of MG-152. Includes three <a href=\"/wiki/Nicol_Amalfi\" title=\"Nicol Amalfi\">Nicol Amalfi</a> figurines (pilot, standing, relaxed). Water slide decal sheet is sold separately with MG <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X13A_Providence_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a> G.U.N.D.A.M. Edition.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>159 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ae/Age-2_boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120803071526\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Age-2 boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Age-2 boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Age-2_boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/ae/Age-2_boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120803071526\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AGE-2_Gundam_AGE-2_Normal\" title=\"AGE-2 Gundam AGE-2 Normal\">Gundam AGE-2 Normal</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_AGE\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam AGE\">Mobile Suit Gundam AGE</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2012 August\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Asemu_Asuno\" title=\"Asemu Asuno\">Asemu Asuno</a> figurine. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>160 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ec/MG_Buster_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120827214723\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Buster Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Buster Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Buster_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ec/MG_Buster_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120827214723\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X103_Buster_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X103 Buster Gundam\">GAT-X103 Buster Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2012 September\n</td>\n<td>Uses the B, C, D, E, and F plate runners of MG-152. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Dearka_Elsman\" title=\"Dearka Elsman\">Dearka Elsman</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately with MG <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X13A_Providence_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a> G.U.N.D.A.M. Edition.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>161 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6c/Aegis_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120927080315\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Aegis Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Aegis Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Aegis_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6c/Aegis_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20120927080315\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X303_Aegis_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X303 Aegis Gundam\">GAT-X303 Aegis Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2012 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Athrun_Zala\" title=\"Athrun Zala\">Athrun Zala</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately with MG <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X13A_Providence_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a> G.U.N.D.A.M. Edition. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>162 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/ff/DarkHound_MG_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150328111256\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"DarkHound MG Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"156\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"DarkHound MG Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"DarkHound_MG_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/ff/DarkHound_MG_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150328111256\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AGE-2DH_Gundam_AGE-2_Dark_Hound\" title=\"AGE-2DH Gundam AGE-2 Dark Hound\">Gundam AGE-2 Dark Hound</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_AGE\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam AGE\">Mobile Suit Gundam AGE</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2012 November\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-159. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Asemu_Asuno\" title=\"Asemu Asuno\">Captain Ash</a> figurine. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>163 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f8/Nu_Gundam_ver_KA_MG_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20121130021050\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Nu Gundam ver KA MG Box Art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Nu Gundam ver KA MG Box Art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Nu_Gundam_ver_KA_MG_Box_Art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f8/Nu_Gundam_ver_KA_MG_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20121130021050\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-93_%CE%BD_Gundam\" title=\"RX-93 \u03bd Gundam\">RX-93 \u03bd Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2012 December\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-034 with improved articulation and proportions. Uses Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner, a new preassembled hand design dual-molded in ABS and polypropylene for high articulation. Features \"Invoke Mode\" gimmick, which consists mainly of a green Psycho-Frame (transformation requires removal of some armor parts). Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> (blue uniform) figurine, an Amuro insignia display base from MG-095, effect parts for the Fin Funnels, and water slide decal sheet. Neck accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). Released to commemorate the 25th anniversary of <i>Char's Counterattack</i>. Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>164 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d5/MG_Tallgesse_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180402145104\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Tallgesse Box Art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Tallgesse Box Art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Tallgesse_Box_Art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d5/MG_Tallgesse_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180402145104\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/OZ-00MS_Tallgeese\" title=\"OZ-00MS Tallgeese\">OZ-00MS Tallgeese</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2013 January\n</td>\n<td>Features the spring-loading gimmick on the Dober Gun. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Zechs_Merquise\" title=\"Zechs Merquise\">Zechs Merquise</a> (TV version) figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>165 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d9/MGSinanjuSteinBoxArt.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20190226141239\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGSinanjuSteinBoxArt\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGSinanjuSteinBoxArt.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MGSinanjuSteinBoxArt.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d9/MGSinanjuSteinBoxArt.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20190226141239\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-06S_Sinanju_Stein\" title=\"MSN-06S Sinanju Stein\">MSN-06S Sinanju Stein \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/UC-MSV\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"UC-MSV\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn MSV</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2013 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-116. Uses Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner. Includes Rocket Bazooka, <a href=\"/wiki/Full_Frontal\" title=\"Full Frontal\">Full Frontal</a> figurine and water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>166 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/82/Rezel_Defenser_MG_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20130228141234\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Rezel Defenser MG Box Art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Rezel Defenser MG Box Art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Rezel_Defenser_MG_Box_Art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/82/Rezel_Defenser_MG_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20130228141234\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGZ-95C_ReZEL_Type_C_(Defenser_B-Unit)_(GR)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RGZ-95C ReZEL Type C (Defenser B-Unit) (GR)\">RGZ-95C ReZEL Type C [Defenser B-Unit] [GR]</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,500\n</td>\n<td>2013 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-139. Includes Earth Federation pilot figurine and extra backpack to create <a href=\"/wiki/RGZ-95C_ReZEL_Commander_Type_(Defenser_A-Unit)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RGZ-95C ReZEL Commander Type (Defenser A-Unit)\">RGZ-95C ReZEL Type C [Defenser A-Unit] [GR]</a>. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>167 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9d/MG_Sinanju_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151113021257\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Sinanju Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Sinanju Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Sinanju_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9d/MG_Sinanju_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151113021257\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-06S_Sinanju\" title=\"MSN-06S Sinanju\">MSN-06S Sinanju (OVA Ver.)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,500\n</td>\n<td>2013 March\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-116, with inner frame materials changed from ABS to polystyrene, hence reducing the risk of peg breakage that modelers experienced with the original kit. Includes Rocket Bazooka of MG-165 with a different handle, which can be combined with the Beam Rifle like in <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Unicorn\" title=\"Black Unicorn\">OVA Episode 5</a>. First MG kit to use entirely polystyrene.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>168 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bd/MG_Jesta_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20130404183236\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Jesta Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Jesta Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Jesta_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bd/MG_Jesta_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20130404183236\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-96X_Jesta\" title=\"RGM-96X Jesta\">RGM-96X Jesta</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2013 April\n</td>\n<td>Uses Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Londo_Bell\" title=\"Londo Bell\">Londo Bell</a> Tri-Stars pilot figurine. Upper torso accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately).\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>169 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/05/MG_Aile_Strike_RM_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20130530063356\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Aile Strike RM Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Aile Strike RM Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Aile_Strike_RM_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/05/MG_Aile_Strike_RM_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20130530063356\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105%2BAQM/E-X01_Aile_Strike_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105+AQM/E-X01 Aile Strike Gundam\">GAT-X105 Aile Strike Gundam Ver.RM</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2013 May\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-065 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Kira_Yamato\" title=\"Kira Yamato\">Kira Yamato</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Mu_La_Flaga\" title=\"Mu La Flaga\">Mu La Flaga</a> figurines, stand from MG-065, MG-090 (Re-color version) and MG-108, and battery pack to create <a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105%2BAQM/E-YM1_Perfect_Strike_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105+AQM/E-YM1 Perfect Strike Gundam\">GAT-X105+AQM/E-YM1 Perfect Strike Gundam</a>. Uses the B, C, D, E, and F plate runners of MG-152. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-91 and bundled with MG <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X13A_Providence_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a> G.U.N.D.A.M. Edition.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>170 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/MG_Age2_Double_Bullet_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20130530063432\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Age2 Double Bullet Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Age2 Double Bullet Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Age2_Double_Bullet_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/55/MG_Age2_Double_Bullet_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20130530063432\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AGE-2DB_Gundam_AGE-2_Double_Bullet\" title=\"AGE-2DB Gundam AGE-2 Double Bullet\">Gundam AGE-2 Double Bullet</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_AGE\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam AGE\">Mobile Suit Gundam AGE</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2013 June\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-159.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>171 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/14/Geara_Doga_MG_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20130626124005\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Geara Doga MG Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"127\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Geara Doga MG Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Geara_Doga_MG_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/14/Geara_Doga_MG_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20130626124005\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AMS-119_Geara_Doga\" title=\"AMS-119 Geara Doga\">AMS-119 Geara Doga</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2013 July\n</td>\n<td>Includes Neo Zeon pilot figurine. Neck accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). Last kit to use the Ver.1.0 box and instruction manual format.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>172 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/33/MG_Rx-78-2_ver_3.0_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20130731134234\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Rx-78-2 ver 3.0 Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Rx-78-2 ver 3.0 Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Rx-78-2_ver_3.0_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/33/MG_Rx-78-2_ver_3.0_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20130731134234\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-2_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-2 Gundam\">RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.3.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2013 August\n</td>\n<td>Uses the D and K plate runners of MG-111, and Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine. Upper torso accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). Beam Javelin, Gundam Hammer and water slide decal sheet are sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit; water slide decal sheet is also sold separately as GD-97.\n<p>First MG Ver.3.0 kit, part of the evolution of the MG Line, where greater articulation is achieved using a new armor on inner frame placement design. Like the <a href=\"/wiki/Real_Grade\" title=\"Real Grade\">RG-01</a> version, this kit is modeled after the 2009 1/1 scale RX-78-2 Gundam statue at Odaiba. Released to commemorate the 35th anniversary of <i>Gundam</i>.\n</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>173 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f2/MG_Strike_Rogue_Ootori.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151127061059\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Strike Rogue Ootori\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Strike Rogue Ootori.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Strike_Rogue_Ootori.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f2/MG_Strike_Rogue_Ootori.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151127061059\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MBF-02%2BEW454F_Strike_Rouge_Ootori\" title=\"MBF-02+EW454F Strike Rouge Ootori\">MBF-02+EW454F Strike Rouge + Ootori Ver.RM</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Desiny Remastered</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2013 September\n</td>\n<td>Color variant of MG-169; redesign of MG-074 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Cagalli_Yula_Athha\" title=\"Cagalli Yula Athha\">Cagalli Yula Athha</a> figurine, and Ootori first seen in the opening of Phase 14 of <i>SEED Destiny</i> Remastered. Compatible with the Aile Striker from MG-169, the I.W.S.P. from MG-090 and MG-104, and both Sword and Launcher Striker from MG-108.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>174 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/45/Master_Grade_Wing_Proto_Zero_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20131003183848\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Master Grade Wing Proto Zero Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Master Grade Wing Proto Zero Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Master_Grade_Wing_Proto_Zero_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/45/Master_Grade_Wing_Proto_Zero_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20131003183848\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-00W0_Wing_Gundam_Proto_Zero\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Proto Zero\">XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Proto Zero EW</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_Glory_of_the_Losers\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: Glory of the Losers\">Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: Glory of the Losers</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2013 October\n</td>\n<td>Includes BA-2 display base with adapter for Neo Bird mode and a <a href=\"/wiki/Heero_Yuy\" title=\"Heero Yuy\">Heero Yuy</a> figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-93. First official Katoki redesign of the Wing Gundam Zero TV Version. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>175 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/db/MG_Sazabi_ver_KA_new_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20131127155308\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Sazabi ver KA new Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"66\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Sazabi ver KA new Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Sazabi_ver_KA_new_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/db/MG_Sazabi_ver_KA_new_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20131127155308\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-04_Sazabi\" title=\"MSN-04 Sazabi\">MSN-04 Sazabi \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a59,000\n</td>\n<td>2013 December\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-029 with improved articulation and proportions. First and currently the only regular release MG kit to use Emotion Manipulator SP (MP2) plate runner, a new hand design using the same dual molding technique as the earlier Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner. Features \"Invoke Mode\", which consists of opening armor hatches. Includes Long Rifle seen in illustrations, <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Char Aznable</a> figurine, and water slide decal sheet. Neck accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). Funnel effect parts are sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>176 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6f/MG_Build_Strike_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151113052916\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Build Strike Box Art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Build Strike Box Art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Build_Strike_Box_Art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6f/MG_Build_Strike_Box_Art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151113052916\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105B/FP_Build_Strike_Gundam_Full_Package\" title=\"GAT-X105B/FP Build Strike Gundam Full Package\">GAT-X105B/FP Build Strike Gundam Full Package</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Fighters\" title=\"Gundam Build Fighters\">Gundam Build Fighters</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2014 January\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-169. Includes Build Booster and multipurpose connector parts for other MG kits, and <a href=\"/wiki/Sei_Iori\" title=\"Sei Iori\">Sei Iori</a> figurine, as well as a leftover <a href=\"/wiki/Kira_Yamato\" title=\"Kira Yamato\">Kira Yamato</a> pilot figure from MG-169. Compatible with all MG Striker packs. First MG kit from the <i>Gundam Build Fighters</i> series.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>177 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bf/MG_Gundam_X_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20131226043045\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam X Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam X Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_X_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/bf/MG_Gundam_X_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20131226043045\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GX-9900_Gundam_X\" title=\"GX-9900 Gundam X\">GX-9900 Gundam X</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/After_War_Gundam_X\" title=\"After War Gundam X\">After War Gundam X</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2014 January\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Garrod_Ran\" title=\"Garrod Ran\">Garrod Ran</a> figurine, clear parts and plated stickers for the Microwave Reflectors. First MG kit from the <a href=\"/wiki/After_War\" title=\"After War\">After War</a> era.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>178 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/dd/MG_Sengoku_Astray_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20140203134649\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Sengoku Astray Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Sengoku Astray Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Sengoku_Astray_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/dd/MG_Sengoku_Astray_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20140203134649\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/%E4%BE%8D%E3%83%8E%E5%BC%90_Sengoku_Astray_Gundam\" title=\"\u4f8d\u30ce\u5f10 Sengoku Astray Gundam\">\u4f8d\u30ce\u5f10 Sengoku Astray Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Fighters\" title=\"Gundam Build Fighters\">Gundam Build Fighters</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2014 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-130. Includes Oni no Tate and multipurpose connector parts for other MG kits, and <a href=\"/wiki/Nils_Yajima\" title=\"Nils Yajima\">Nils Nielsen</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>179 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b4/MG_Unicorn_Phenex.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20140127055541\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Unicorn Phenex\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Unicorn Phenex.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Unicorn_Phenex.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b4/MG_Unicorn_Phenex.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20140127055541\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam_03_Phenex\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 03 Phenex\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 03 Phenex</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_UC:_One_of_Seventy_Two\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam UC: One of Seventy Two\">Mobile Suit Gundam UC: One of Seventy Two</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a512,000\n</td>\n<td>2014 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-155. Includes water slide decal sheet and a leftover <a href=\"/wiki/Banagher_Links\" title=\"Banagher Links\">Banagher Links</a> figurine from MG-102. First regular release chrome plated MG kit since MG-037.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>180 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0c/MG_Build_Gundam_MK2_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20140228102936\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Build Gundam MK2 Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Build Gundam MK2 Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Build_Gundam_MK2_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0c/MG_Build_Gundam_MK2_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20140228102936\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-178B_Build_Gundam_Mk-II\" title=\"RX-178B Build Gundam Mk-II\">RX-178B Build Gundam Mk-II</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Fighters\" title=\"Gundam Build Fighters\">Gundam Build Fighters</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2014 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-082. Launchpad replaced by MG Build Booster Mk-II. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Reiji\" title=\"Reiji\">Reiji</a> and the original kit's figurines, as well as multipurpose connector parts for other MG kits.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>181 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0e/MG_Universal_Booster_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20140228102907\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Universal Booster Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"160\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Universal Booster Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Universal_Booster_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0e/MG_Universal_Booster_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20140228102907\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105B/ST_Star_Build_Strike_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105B/ST Star Build Strike Gundam\">UB-01 Universe Booster</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Fighters\" title=\"Gundam Build Fighters\">Gundam Build Fighters</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,800\n</td>\n<td>2014 March\n</td>\n<td>Accessory kit for MG-176. Includes BA-1 display base, extra parts to convert MG-176 into <a href=\"/wiki/GAT-X105B/ST_Star_Build_Strike_Gundam\" title=\"GAT-X105B/ST Star Build Strike Gundam\">GAT-X105B/ST Star Build Strike Gundam</a>, effect parts, and multipurpose connector parts for other MG kits.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>182 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1d/MG_Turn_X_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150328030216\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Turn X Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Turn X Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Turn_X_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1d/MG_Turn_X_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150328030216\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Concept-X_6-1-2_Turn_X\" title=\"Concept-X 6-1-2 Turn X\">Concept-X 6-1-2 Turn X</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/%E2%88%80_Gundam\" title=\"\u2200 Gundam\">\u2200 Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2014 June\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Gym_Ghingham\" title=\"Gym Ghingham\">Gym Ghingham</a> figurine, custom stand for \"Bloody Siege\" attack, and effect part for \"Shining Finger\". Uses entirely polystyrene except for the stand, which is ABS.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>183 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9c/MG_Hi-v_ver.ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20140808163549\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Hi-v ver.ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Hi-v ver.ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Hi-v_ver.ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9c/MG_Hi-v_ver.ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20140808163549\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-93-%CE%BD2_Hi-%CE%BD_Gundam\" title=\"RX-93-\u03bd2 Hi-\u03bd Gundam\">RX-93-\u03bd2 Hi-\u03bd Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack_-_Beltorchika%27s_Children\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack - Beltorchika&#39;s Children\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2014 August\n</td>\n<td>Uses the F, I, and R plate runners of MG-163, and Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner; redesign of MG-095 with improved articulation and proportions closer to the original lineart. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray\" title=\"Amuro Ray\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine, an Amuro insignia display base from MG-095, prop stand for backpack, effect parts for the Fin Funnels, and water slide decal sheet. Neck accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>184 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e7/MG_Astray_Blue_Frame_D_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20160308044732\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Astray Blue Frame D Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Astray Blue Frame D Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Astray_Blue_Frame_D_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e7/MG_Astray_Blue_Frame_D_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20160308044732\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MBF-P03D_Gundam_Astray_Blue_Frame_D\" title=\"MBF-P03D Gundam Astray Blue Frame D\">MBF-P03D Gundam Astray Blue Frame D</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny_Astray_B\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny Astray B\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny Astray B</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2014 November\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-125. Includes display base and <a href=\"/wiki/Gai_Murakumo\" title=\"Gai Murakumo\">Gai Murakumo</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Elsa_Weiss\" title=\"Elsa Weiss\">Elsa Weiss</a> figurines. Formation Base for DRAGOON units is sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>185 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/cf/MG_Exia_Dark_Matter_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150411104743\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Exia Dark Matter Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Exia Dark Matter Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Exia_Dark_Matter_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/cf/MG_Exia_Dark_Matter_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150411104743\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/PPGN-001_Gundam_Exia_Dark_Matter\" title=\"PPGN-001 Gundam Exia Dark Matter\">PPGN-001 Gundam Exia Dark Matter</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Fighters\" title=\"Gundam Build Fighters\">Gundam Build Fighters</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2015 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-123. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Tatsuya_Yuuki\" title=\"Tatsuya Yuuki\">Meijin Kawaguchi the 3rd</a> figurine, Dark Matter Booster and multipurpose connector parts for other MG kits. Dark Matter Booster accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately).\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>186 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/eb/MG_Gundam_Double_X.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150326081528\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam Double X\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam Double X.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_Double_X.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/eb/MG_Gundam_Double_X.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150326081528\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GX-9901-DX_Gundam_Double_X\" title=\"GX-9901-DX Gundam Double X\">GX-9901-DX Gundam Double X</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/After_War_Gundam_X\" title=\"After War Gundam X\">After War Gundam X</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2015 March\n</td>\n<td>Uses the B and C plate runners of MG-177. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Garrod_Ran\" title=\"Garrod Ran\">Garrod Ran</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Tiffa_Adill\" title=\"Tiffa Adill\">Tiffa Adill</a> figurines, clear parts and plated stickers for the Microwave Reflectors. Compatible with <a href=\"/wiki/GS-9900_G-Falcon\" title=\"GS-9900 G-Falcon\">GS-9900 G-Falcon</a> from <a href=\"/wiki/1/100_High_Grade_Gundam_X_Model_Series\" title=\"1/100 High Grade Gundam X Model Series\">HGGX</a>-08.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>187 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d4/MG_Hyaku_Shiki_Ver._2.0.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150428034242\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Hyaku Shiki Ver. 2.0\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Hyaku Shiki Ver. 2.0.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Hyaku_Shiki_Ver._2.0.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d4/MG_Hyaku_Shiki_Ver._2.0.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150428034242\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-00100_Hyaku_Shiki\" title=\"MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki\">MSN-00100 Hyaku-Shiki Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,800\n</td>\n<td>2015 May\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-037 with improved articulation and proportions. Armor pieces feature metallic gold painted over clear white plastic. Includes two <a href=\"/wiki/Char_Aznable\" title=\"Char Aznable\">Quattro Bajeena</a> figurines, and parts to attach to Ballute System. Shares weapon parts with <a href=\"/wiki/Reborn-One_Hundred\" title=\"Reborn-One Hundred\">RE-04</a>. Mega Bazooka Launcher and water slide decal sheet is sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit. Released to commemorate the 30th anniversary of <i>Zeta Gundam</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>188 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e3/MG_Gundam_Fenice_Rinascita.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150529093602\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam Fenice Rinascita\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam Fenice Rinascita.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_Fenice_Rinascita.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e3/MG_Gundam_Fenice_Rinascita.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150529093602\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01Wfr_Gundam_Fenice_Rinascita\" title=\"XXXG-01Wfr Gundam Fenice Rinascita\">XXXG-01Wfr Gundam Fenice Rinascita</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Fighters\" title=\"Gundam Build Fighters\">Gundam Build Fighters</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2015 June\n</td>\n<td>Uses the F, G, and H plate runners of MG-132. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Ricardo_Fellini\" title=\"Ricardo Fellini\">Ricardo Fellini</a> figurine and a redesigned BA-13 Action Base 1. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>189<figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8e/Mg_Gundam_Amazing_Red_Warrior.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20150731143542\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg Gundam Amazing Red Warrior\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg Gundam Amazing Red Warrior.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_Gundam_Amazing_Red_Warrior.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8e/Mg_Gundam_Amazing_Red_Warrior.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20150731143542\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/PF-78-3A_Gundam_Amazing_Red_Warrior\" title=\"PF-78-3A Gundam Amazing Red Warrior\">PF-78-3A Gundam Amazing Red Warrior</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Fighters_Try\" title=\"Gundam Build Fighters Try\">Gundam Build Fighters Try</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2015 August\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-111. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Tatsuya_Yuuki\" title=\"Tatsuya Yuuki\">Meijin Kawaguchi the 3rd</a> figurine. First MG kit from the <i>Gundam Build Fighters Try</i> series.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>190 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/65/MG-GundamOrigin.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151113052649\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG-GundamOrigin\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG-GundamOrigin.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG-GundamOrigin.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/65/MG-GundamOrigin.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151113052649\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78-02_Gundam\" title=\"RX-78-02 Gundam\">RX-78-02 Gundam The Origin</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_Origin_(Manga)\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: The Origin (Manga)\">Mobile Suit Gundam: The Origin</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,600\n</td>\n<td>2015 November\n</td>\n<td>Uses the I plate runner of MG-111, and Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Amuro_Ray_(Origin)\" title=\"Amuro Ray (Origin)\">Amuro Ray</a> figurine, and effect parts for the shoulder and forearm guns. Upper torso accommodates Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately). First MG kit from the <i>Mobile Suit Gundam: The Origin</i> series.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>191 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2d/MG_Victory_2_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20151202082042\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Victory 2 Gundam Ver.Ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Victory 2 Gundam Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Victory_2_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2d/MG_Victory_2_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20151202082042\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/LM314V21_Victory_2_Gundam\" title=\"LM314V21 Victory 2 Gundam\">LM314V21 Victory Two Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Victory_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Victory Gundam\">Mobile Suit Victory Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2015 December\n</td>\n<td>Includes two Gundam heads, two Core Fighters with clear attachments for <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_1\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 1</a>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Shahkti_Kareen\" title=\"Shahkti Kareen\">Shahkti Kareen</a> figurine, and water slide decal sheet. \"Wings of Light\" effect parts are sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>192 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0e/MGFreedomGundam2.0.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20160401125320\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGFreedomGundam2.0\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGFreedomGundam2.0.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MGFreedomGundam2.0.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/0e/MGFreedomGundam2.0.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20160401125320\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X10A_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2016 April\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-072 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes BA-2 display base and <a href=\"/wiki/Kira_Yamato\" title=\"Kira Yamato\">Kira Yamato</a> figurine. Effect parts and water slide decal sheet are sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit; water slide decal sheet is also bundled with MG <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X13A_Providence_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a> G.U.N.D.A.M. Edition. Uses entirely polystyrene. Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>193 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/af/MG_Full_Armor_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20190227133211\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Full Armor Gundam Ver.Ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Full Armor Gundam Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Full_Armor_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/af/MG_Full_Armor_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20190227133211\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/FA-78_Full_Armor_Gundam_(Thunderbolt_Ver.)\" title=\"FA-78 Full Armor Gundam (Thunderbolt Ver.)\">FA-78 Full Armor Gundam [Gundam Thunderbolt] \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Thunderbolt\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt\">Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2016 July\n</td>\n<td>Features polyethylene joint seals and a functional emergency pod. Includes display base, <a href=\"/wiki/Io_Fleming\" title=\"Io Fleming\">Io Fleming</a> figurine, and water slide decal sheet. Beam Rifle and Hyper Bazooka are sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit. Released to coincide with the Blu-ray release of <i>Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt: December Sky</i>. Reissues from 2024 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>194 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/96/Mg-psychozaku.png/revision/latest?cb=20170529095819\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-psychozaku\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"67\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-psychozaku.png\" data-image-key=\"Mg-psychozaku.png\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/96/Mg-psychozaku.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20170529095819\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-06R_Zaku_High_Mobility_Type_(Reuse_%22P%22_Device)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MS-06R Zaku High Mobility Type (Reuse &quot;P&quot; Device)\">MS-06R Zaku II High Mobility Type \"Psycho Zaku\" [Gundam Thunderbolt] \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Thunderbolt\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt\">Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a59,000\n</td>\n<td>2016 December\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-103. Features polyethylene joint seals. Includes Base 5 display base, stand for propellant tank, <a href=\"/wiki/Daryl_Lorenz\" title=\"Daryl Lorenz\">Daryl Lorenz</a> figurine, and water slide decal sheet (metallic silver in initial releases of the kit). First MG kit to have bilingual Japanese/English text on its box packaging and instruction manual.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>195 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/62/MGGMSniperII.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20161221093930\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGGMSniperII\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGGMSniperII.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MGGMSniperII.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/62/MGGMSniperII.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20161221093930\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79SP_GM_Sniper_II\" title=\"RGM-79SP GM Sniper II\">RGM-79SP GM Sniper II</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0080:_War_in_the_Pocket\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,800\n</td>\n<td>2017 January\n</td>\n<td>Uses the H, I, and J plate runners of MG-111 and the MP plate runner of MG-153. Features WP plate runner, which is a universal weapons runner for some MG Earth Federation kits. Includes Earth Federation pilot figurine. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-118.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>196 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/73/MG_Providence.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20250307031437\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Providence\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Providence.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Providence.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/7/73/MG_Providence.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20250307031437\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X13A_Providence_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2017 March\n</td>\n<td>Uses the I and J plate runners of MG-192. Uses entirely polystyrene except for the cables, which are TPE. Includes effect parts for DRAGOON units, BA-2 display base, and <a href=\"/wiki/Rau_Le_Creuset\" title=\"Rau Le Creuset\">Rau Le Creuset</a> figurine. Additional effect parts for DRAGOON units and water slide decal sheet are sold separately as P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>197 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/11/Mg_justice_gundam.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20170529095905\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg justice gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg justice gundam.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg_justice_gundam.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/11/Mg_justice_gundam.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20170529095905\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X09A_Justice_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam\">ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,800\n</td>\n<td>2017 June\n</td>\n<td>Uses the I and J plate runners of MG-192. Includes BA-13 Action Base 1, Action Base 1 adapters for the Gundam and Fatum-00 unit, and <a href=\"/wiki/Athrun_Zala\" title=\"Athrun Zala\">Athrun Zala</a> figurine. Uses entirely polystyrene.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>198 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2c/MG_ZZ_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20170913040036\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG ZZ Gundam Ver.Ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG ZZ Gundam Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_ZZ_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2c/MG_ZZ_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20170913040036\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-010_%CE%96%CE%96_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-010 \u0396\u0396 Gundam\">MSZ-010 ZZ Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_ZZ\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ\">Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2017 September\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-026 with improved articulation and proportions. Features silver metallic detail parts. Includes two transformable <a href=\"/wiki/FXA-07GB_Neo_Core_Fighter\" title=\"FXA-07GB Neo Core Fighter\">FXA-07GB Neo Core Fighters</a>, Action Base 1 adapter for Core Top, <a href=\"/wiki/Judau_Ashta\" title=\"Judau Ashta\">Judau Ashta</a> figurine (Double Beam Rifle features <a href=\"/wiki/Iino_Abbav\" title=\"Iino Abbav\">Iino Abbav</a> figurine), and water slide decal sheet. Released to commemorate the 30th anniversary of <i>Gundam ZZ</i>. Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>199 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e7/MG_GM_Sniper_Custom.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20171024072429\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG GM Sniper Custom\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG GM Sniper Custom.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_GM_Sniper_Custom.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e7/MG_GM_Sniper_Custom.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20171024072429\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79SC_GM_Sniper_Custom\" title=\"RGM-79SC GM Sniper Custom\">RGM-79SC GM Sniper Custom</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Variation\" title=\"Mobile Suit Variation\">Mobile Suit Variation</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2017 November\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-118. Includes Earth Federation pilot figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>200 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/fd/MG_GM_Command_-Colony_Type-.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20171228110747\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG GM Command -Colony Type-\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"155\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG GM Command -Colony Type-.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_GM_Command_-Colony_Type-.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/fd/MG_GM_Command_-Colony_Type-.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20171228110747\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79G_GM_Command\" title=\"RGM-79G GM Command\">RGM-79G GM Command (Colony Type)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0080:_War_in_the_Pocket\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2017 December\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-195. Color variant of MG <a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79GS_GM_Command_Space_Type\" title=\"RGM-79GS GM Command Space Type\">RGM-79GS GM Command Space</a> with a different backpack. Water slide decal sheet is sold separately as GD-118. The 200th MG release. Originally planned to be released in January 2018.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>3<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>201 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3d/MG_Unicorn_Gundam_02_Banshee_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180309020849\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee Ver.Ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Unicorn_Gundam_02_Banshee_Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3d/MG_Unicorn_Gundam_02_Banshee_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180309020849\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam_02_Banshee\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn_(Novel)\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn (Novel)\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i> (Novel)\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2018 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-102; F plate runners are renewed for improved knee articulation. Re-release of MG RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee \"Ver.Ka\" (Final Battle Ver.) with yellow Psycho-Frame. Includes water slide decal sheet and a leftover <a href=\"/wiki/Banagher_Links\" title=\"Banagher Links\">Banagher Links</a> figurine from MG-102, but no <a href=\"/wiki/Marida_Cruz\" title=\"Marida Cruz\">Marida Cruz</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Riddhe_Marcenas\" title=\"Riddhe Marcenas\">Riddhe Marcenas</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>202 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f3/MG_Plan_303E_Deep_Striker.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180309021025\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Plan 303E Deep Striker\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Plan 303E Deep Striker.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Plan_303E_Deep_Striker.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f3/MG_Plan_303E_Deep_Striker.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180309021025\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSA-0011%EF%BC%BBBst%EF%BC%BD_S_Gundam_Booster_Unit_Type_Plan_303E_%22Deep_Striker%22\" title=\"MSA-0011\uff3bBst\uff3d S Gundam Booster Unit Type Plan 303E &quot;Deep Striker&quot;\">MSA-0011[Bst] Plan303E Deep Striker</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a520,000\n</td>\n<td>2018 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-060. Includes display base. Released to commemorate the 30th anniversary of <i>Gundam Sentinel</i>. Largest MG release to date.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>203 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/03/MG_F91_Gundam_Ver._2.0.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180514124050\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG F91 Gundam Ver. 2.0\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG F91 Gundam Ver. 2.0.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_F91_Gundam_Ver._2.0.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/0/03/MG_F91_Gundam_Ver._2.0.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180514124050\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/F91_Gundam_F91\" title=\"F91 Gundam F91\">F91 Gundam F91 Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_F91\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam F91\">Mobile Suit Gundam F91</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2018 May\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-087 with improved articulation and proportions. Features metallic detail parts. Includes two heads (transformable and non-transformable), <a href=\"/wiki/Cecily_Fairchild\" title=\"Cecily Fairchild\">Cecily Fairchild</a> figurine, and a gray custom base using a black <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base</a> 4/5 hexagon as platform. Chest vents and backpack thrusters accommodate Gunpla Lighting Unit (sold separately) via the custom base. Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>204 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b0/MG_Jegan.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180713111011\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Jegan\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Jegan.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Jegan.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/b/b0/MG_Jegan.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180713111011\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RGM-89_Jegan\" title=\"RGM-89 Jegan\">RGM-89 Jegan</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Char&#39;s Counterattack\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,000\n</td>\n<td>2018 July\n</td>\n<td>Uses the MP plate runner of MG-153. Uses entirely polystyrene. Unlike majority of the MG kits, no character figurine is included. Released to commemorate the 30th anniversary of <i>Char's Counterattack</i> and as part of Bandai's <i>\"UC NexT 0100\" project</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>205 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e9/MG_00_Qan-T-_Full_Saber.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180906104907\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG 00 Qan-T- Full Saber\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG 00 Qan-T- Full Saber.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_00_Qan-T-_Full_Saber.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e9/MG_00_Qan-T-_Full_Saber.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20180906104907\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GNT-0000/FS_00_Qan%EF%BC%BBT%EF%BC%BD_Full_Saber\" title=\"GNT-0000/FS 00 Qan\uff3bT\uff3d Full Saber\">GNT-0000/FS 00 Qan[T] Full Saber</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00V:_Battlefield_Record\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00V: Battlefield Record\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00V: Battlefield Record</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,500\n</td>\n<td>2018 September\n</td>\n<td>Re-release of MG-140 with GN Sword IV Full Saber, new antenna and a modified backpack unit, but without Action Base 2. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Setsuna_F._Seiei\" title=\"Setsuna F. Seiei\">Setsuna F. Seiei</a> figurine and clear <a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base#Action_Base_5\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base 5</a> for GN Sword IV Full Saber. GN Drive accommodates two Gunpla LED Units (sold separately). Released to commemorate the 10th anniversary of <i>Gundam 00</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>206 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/34/MG_Sinanju_Stein_%28Narrative_Ver.%29.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20190118040648\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Sinanju Stein (Narrative Ver.)\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Sinanju Stein (Narrative Ver.).jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Sinanju_Stein_%28Narrative_Ver.%29.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/34/MG_Sinanju_Stein_%28Narrative_Ver.%29.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20190118040648\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-06S-2_Sinanju_Stein\" title=\"MSN-06S-2 Sinanju Stein\">MSN-06S-2 Sinanju Stein (Narrative Ver.)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Narrative\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Narrative\">Mobile Suit Gundam Narrative</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,500\n</td>\n<td>2019 January\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-165 with <a href=\"/wiki/Sleeves\" title=\"Sleeves\">Sleeves</a> markings, and redesigned shield and propellant tanks. Uses Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner. Includes Grenade Launcher attachment for High Beam Rifle or shield, and Rocket Bazooka can be combined with High Beam Rifle as with MG-167. Includes leftover <a href=\"/wiki/Full_Frontal\" title=\"Full Frontal\">Full Frontal</a> pilot and standing figurines, but no <a href=\"/wiki/Zoltan_Akkanen\" title=\"Zoltan Akkanen\">Zoltan Akkanen</a> figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>207 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/62/MG_Gundam_Dynames.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20190308103936\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam Dynames\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam Dynames.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_Dynames.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/62/MG_Gundam_Dynames.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20190308103936\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GN-002_Gundam_Dynames\" title=\"GN-002 Gundam Dynames\">GN-002 Gundam Dynames</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2019 March\n</td>\n<td>Uses entirely polystyrene, except for the GN Cables, which are EVAC. GN Drive accommodates two Gunpla LED Units (sold separately). Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Lockon_Stratos_(Neil_Dylandy)\" title=\"Lockon Stratos (Neil Dylandy)\">Lockon Stratos</a> (with <a href=\"/wiki/Haro_(Anno_Domini)\" title=\"Haro (Anno Domini)\">Haro</a>) figurine.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>208 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/80/MG_Gundam_AgeII_Magnum.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20190308104021\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam AgeII Magnum\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam AgeII Magnum.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_AgeII_Magnum.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/80/MG_Gundam_AgeII_Magnum.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20190308104021\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/AGE-IIMG_Gundam_AGEII_Magnum\" title=\"AGE-IIMG Gundam AGEII Magnum\">AGE-IIMG Gundam AGEII Magnum</a>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Build_Divers\" title=\"Gundam Build Divers\">Gundam Build Divers</a>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,500\n</td>\n<td>2019 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-159, with shoulder joints revised for improved articulation and stability. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Kyoya_Kujo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kyoya Kujo\">Kyoya Kujo</a> figruine, as well as a leftover <a href=\"/wiki/Asemu_Asuno\" title=\"Asemu Asuno\">Asemu Asuno</a> figurine from the original kit. Fully transformable kit. First release from the <a href=\"/wiki/Build_Divers\" title=\"Build Divers\">Build Divers</a> timeline.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>209 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4d/MG_Ex-S_Gundam_S_Gundam.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20250307032320\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Ex-S Gundam S Gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Ex-S Gundam S Gundam.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Ex-S_Gundam_S_Gundam.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/4/4d/MG_Ex-S_Gundam_S_Gundam.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20250307032320\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSA-0011%EF%BC%BBExt%EF%BC%BD_Ex-S_Gundam\" title=\"MSA-0011\uff3bExt\uff3d Ex-S Gundam\">MSA-0011[Ext] Ex-S Gundam</a> / <a href=\"/wiki/MSA-0011_S_Gundam\" title=\"MSA-0011 S Gundam\">MSA-0011 S Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a512,000\n</td>\n<td>2019 April\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-055 and MG-060; enhanced version of both kits with improved details (<i>de facto</i> Ver.1.5 in <a href=\"/wiki/Hajime_Katoki\" title=\"Hajime Katoki\">Hajime Katoki</a>'s original design color scheme but not labelled); either of the two units can be built at any time. Uses head, shoulder, chest, and backpack of MG-202 with redesigned abdomen parts and new fixed hands for various poses. Transforms via complex parts-forming. Includes clear display base, cables for INCOM units, and a marking sheet designed by Hajime Katoki.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>210 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/92/MG_Gundam_NT-1_Ver.2.0.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20190627015525\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam NT-1 Ver.2.0\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam NT-1 Ver.2.0.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_NT-1_Ver.2.0.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/92/MG_Gundam_NT-1_Ver.2.0.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20190627015525\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-78NT-1_Gundam_NT-1\" title=\"RX-78NT-1 Gundam NT-1\">RX-78NT-1 Gundam NT-1 Ver.2.0</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_0080:_War_in_the_Pocket\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket\">Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,800\n</td>\n<td>2019 June\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-022 with improved articulation and proportions; uses the K plate runner of MG-111. Features polyethylene joint seals. Includes hyper bazooka, broken V-fin as seen in <a href=\"/wiki/Over_the_River_and_Through_the_Woods\" title=\"Over the River and Through the Woods\">episode 4</a> of the OVA, optional headgear based on the <a href=\"/wiki/SD_Gundam_BB_Senshi\" title=\"SD Gundam BB Senshi\">SD Gundam BB Senshi</a> versions, and <a href=\"/wiki/Alfred_Izuruha\" title=\"Alfred Izuruha\">Alfred Izuruha</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Bernard_Wiseman\" title=\"Bernard Wiseman\">Bernard Wiseman</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Christina_Mackenzie\" title=\"Christina Mackenzie\">Christina Mackenzie</a> (pilot suit) figurines. Released to commemorate the 30th anniversary of <i>Gundam 0080</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>211 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8d/MG_Gunner_ZAKU_Warrior_%28Lunamaria_Hawke_Custom%29.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20190926193337\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gunner ZAKU Warrior (Lunamaria Hawke Custom)\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gunner ZAKU Warrior (Lunamaria Hawke Custom).jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gunner_ZAKU_Warrior_%28Lunamaria_Hawke_Custom%29.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8d/MG_Gunner_ZAKU_Warrior_%28Lunamaria_Hawke_Custom%29.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20190926193337\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-1000/A1_Gunner_ZAKU_Warrior\" title=\"ZGMF-1000/A1 Gunner ZAKU Warrior\">ZGMF-1000/A1 Gunner ZAKU Warrior (Lunamaria Hawke Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,300\n</td>\n<td>2019 September\n</td>\n<td>Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Lunamaria_Hawke\" title=\"Lunamaria Hawke\">Lunamaria Hawke</a> figurine. Leg hoses are preassembled using ABS-PP dual-molding technique. Uses entirely polystyrene except for the leg and backpack hoses. Released to commemorate the 15th anniversary of <i>Gundam SEED Destiny</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>212 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8a/Mg-gundam-barbatos_box_art.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20191217102055\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"Mg-gundam-barbatos box art\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Mg-gundam-barbatos box art.jpg\" data-image-key=\"Mg-gundam-barbatos_box_art.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8a/Mg-gundam-barbatos_box_art.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20191217102055\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ASW-G-08_Gundam_Barbatos\" title=\"ASW-G-08 Gundam Barbatos\">ASW-G-08 Gundam Barbatos</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_IRON-BLOODED_ORPHANS\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS\">Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,500\n</td>\n<td>2019 December\n</td>\n<td>Uses entirely polystyrene. Features plated sliver cylinders and gold inner frame parts; clear green parts for eyes and clear pink parts for emblems. Mace features two detachable blades. Includes Smoothbore Gun and <a href=\"/wiki/Mikazuki_Augus\" title=\"Mikazuki Augus\">Mikazuki Augus</a> figurine. First release from the <a href=\"/wiki/Post_Disaster\" title=\"Post Disaster\">Post Disaster</a> timeline. Originally planned to be released in November 2019, but was delayed due to unspecified reasons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>4<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>213 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a3/MG_FAZZ_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20200206094405\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG FAZZ Ver.Ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG FAZZ Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_FAZZ_Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a3/MG_FAZZ_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20200206094405\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/FA-010A_FAZZ\" title=\"FA-010A FAZZ\">FA-010A FAZZ \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Sentinel\" title=\"Gundam Sentinel\">Gundam Sentinel</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a511,000\n</td>\n<td>2020 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-198; redesign of MG-042 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes water slide decal sheet. Uses H2 runner from MG-151, and parts of J1, J2, K1, and K2 runners from P-Bandai exclusive MG Enhanced ZZ Ver. Ka.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>214 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1c/MG_Gundam_Kyrios.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20200518134041\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam Kyrios\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam Kyrios.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_Kyrios.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/1c/MG_Gundam_Kyrios.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20200518134041\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GN-003_Gundam_Kyrios\" title=\"GN-003 Gundam Kyrios\">GN-003 Gundam Kyrios</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2020 May\n</td>\n<td>Includes two GN Hand Missile Units and <a href=\"/wiki/Allelujah_Haptism\" title=\"Allelujah Haptism\">Allelujah Haptism</a> figurine. GN Drive accommodates two Gunpla LED Units (sold separately). Fully transformable kit.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>215 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a8/MG_Wing_Gundam_Zero_EW_VerKa.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20201119081247\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Wing Gundam Zero EW VerKa\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Wing Gundam Zero EW VerKa.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Wing_Gundam_Zero_EW_VerKa.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/a/a8/MG_Wing_Gundam_Zero_EW_VerKa.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20201119081247\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-00W0_Wing_Gundam_Zero_EW\" title=\"XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero EW\">XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero EW \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing:_Endless_Waltz\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,500\n</td>\n<td>2020 November\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-075 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes black BA-13 Action Base 1, and <a href=\"/wiki/Heero_Yuy\" title=\"Heero Yuy\">Heero Yuy</a> figurine. Released to commemorate the 25th anniversary of <i>Gundam Wing</i>. Fully transformable kit. Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>216 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/52/MG_Mobile_Ginn.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20210416110736\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Mobile Ginn\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Mobile Ginn.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Mobile_Ginn.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/52/MG_Mobile_Ginn.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20210416110736\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-1017_GINN\" title=\"ZGMF-1017 GINN\">ZGMF-1017 Mobile Ginn</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a54,300\n</td>\n<td>2021 April\n</td>\n<td>Uses the C and D plate runners of MG-211. Includes ZAFT pilot figurine. Uses entirely polystyrene.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>217 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/dc/MG-Eclipse-Gundam.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20210818014435\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG-Eclipse-Gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG-Eclipse-Gundam.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG-Eclipse-Gundam.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/dc/MG-Eclipse-Gundam.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20210818014435\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MVF-X08_Eclipse_Gundam\" title=\"MVF-X08 Eclipse Gundam\">MVF-X08 Eclipse Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Eclipse\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Eclipse\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Eclipse</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2021 August\n</td>\n<td>Uses the I and J plate runners of MG-192 and entirely polystyrene. Includes black BA-13 Action Base 1. Fully transformable kit. Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>218 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6c/MG_Gundam_Virtue.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20211123035301\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam Virtue\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"54\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam Virtue.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_Virtue.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6c/MG_Gundam_Virtue.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20211123035301\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/GN-005_Gundam_Virtue\" title=\"GN-005 Gundam Virtue\">GN-005 Gundam Virtue</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_00\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam 00\">Mobile Suit Gundam 00</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a58,000\n</td>\n<td>2021 November\n</td>\n<td>Removal of armor parts reveals <a href=\"/wiki/GN-004_Gundam_Nadleeh\" title=\"GN-004 Gundam Nadleeh\">GN-004 Gundam Nadleeh</a>. Includes two <a href=\"/wiki/Tieria_Erde\" title=\"Tieria Erde\">Tieria Erde</a> (pilot suit and evening gown) figurines. GN Drive accommodates one Gunpla LED Unit (sold separately).\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>219 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6a/MG_Dom.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20220207084529\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Dom\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Dom.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Dom.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/6/6a/MG_Dom.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20220207084529\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-09_Dom\" title=\"MS-09 Dom\">MS-09 Dom</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2022 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-021; enhanced version of the kit with revised inner frame from P-Bandai exclusive MG <a href=\"/wiki/MS-09G_Dwadge\" title=\"MS-09G Dwadge\">MS-09G Dwadge</a> and some revised armor pieces (<i>de facto</i> Ver.1.5 but not labelled). Uses Emotion Manipulator SP (MP2) plate runner. Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>220 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e1/MG_Rick_Dom.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20220307093104\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Rick Dom\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Rick Dom.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Rick_Dom.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/e1/MG_Rick_Dom.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20220307093104\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MS-09R_Rick_Dom\" title=\"MS-09R Rick Dom\">MS-09R Rick Dom</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam\">Mobile Suit Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a55,000\n</td>\n<td>2022 March\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-219; enhanced version of MG-023 with revised inner frame from P-Bandai exclusive MG <a href=\"/wiki/MS-09G_Dwadge\" title=\"MS-09G Dwadge\">MS-09G Dwadge</a> and some revised armor pieces (<i>de facto</i> Ver.1.5 but not labelled). Uses Emotion Manipulator SP (MP2) plate runner.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>221 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9a/MG_Zeta_Gundam_VerKa.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20230316095909\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Zeta Gundam VerKa\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Zeta Gundam VerKa.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Zeta_Gundam_VerKa.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9a/MG_Zeta_Gundam_VerKa.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20230316095909\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-006_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam\">MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam\">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,500\n</td>\n<td>2023 April\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-083 with improved articulation and anime-accurate proportions. Fully transformable kit. Features metallic silver frame parts and fully functional landing gear in Wave Rider mode. Includes Grenade Launcher packs and <a href=\"/wiki/Kamille_Bidan\" title=\"Kamille Bidan\">Kamille Bidan</a> figurine. Released to commemorate the 20th anniversary of the Ver.Ka label. Originally planned to be released in February 2023, but was delayed due to unspecified reasons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>5<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>222 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/97/MG_Narrative_Gundam_C-Packs_VerKa.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20240412100418\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Narrative Gundam C-Packs VerKa\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Narrative Gundam C-Packs VerKa.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Narrative_Gundam_C-Packs_VerKa.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/97/MG_Narrative_Gundam_C-Packs_VerKa.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20240412100418\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-9/C_Narrative_Gundam_C-Packs\" title=\"RX-9/C Narrative Gundam C-Packs\">RX-9/C Narrative Gundam C-Packs \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Narrative\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Narrative\">Mobile Suit Gundam Narrative</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2024 April\n</td>\n<td>Includes transformable Core Fighter, Beam Rifle with addtional parts to convert to <a href=\"/wiki/RGM-89_Jegan\" title=\"RGM-89 Jegan\">Jegan</a>'s Beam Rifle, parts to create <a href=\"/wiki/RX-9_Narrative_Gundam\" title=\"RX-9 Narrative Gundam\">RX-9 Narrative Gundam</a> and RX-9/C Narrative Gundam C-Packs (NT-D Deactivated), <a href=\"/wiki/Jona_Basta\" title=\"Jona Basta\">Jona Basta</a> figurine, and water slide decal sheet. Psycho-Frame also compatible with MG-102 and all other variants of MG <a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>223 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8b/MG_Sinanju_Stein_Narrative_Ver_VerKa.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20240412100439\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Sinanju Stein Narrative Ver VerKa\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Sinanju Stein Narrative Ver VerKa.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Sinanju_Stein_Narrative_Ver_VerKa.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/8b/MG_Sinanju_Stein_Narrative_Ver_VerKa.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20240412100439\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/MSN-06S-2_Sinanju_Stein\" title=\"MSN-06S-2 Sinanju Stein\">MSN-06S-2 Sinanju Stein (Narrative Ver.) \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Narrative\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Narrative\">Mobile Suit Gundam Narrative</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a58,000\n</td>\n<td>2024 June\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-206. <a href=\"/wiki/Sleeves\" title=\"Sleeves\">Sleeves</a> markings have been changed from stickers to separate color-coded parts. Includes scope parts to build Beam Rifle instead of High Beam Rifle, Large Beam Axe, <a href=\"/wiki/Zoltan_Akkanen\" title=\"Zoltan Akkanen\">Zoltan Akkanen</a> figurine, and water slide decal sheet. Shield has been redesigned to accommodate Large Beam Axe.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>224 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9d/MGVidar.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20250316182325\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGVidar\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGVidar.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"MGVidar.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/9d/MGVidar.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20250316182325\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ASW-G-XX_Gundam_Vidar\" title=\"ASW-G-XX Gundam Vidar\">ASW-G-XX Gundam Vidar</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_IRON-BLOODED_ORPHANS\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS\">Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2025 March\n</td>\n<td>Handguns feature movable slides. Rifle features detachable magazine. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Gaelio_Bauduin\" title=\"Gaelio Bauduin\">Gaelio Bauduin</a> (standing and sitting) figurines. Released to commemorate the 10th anniversary of <i>Gundam Iron-Blooded Orphans</i>.\n</td>\n<td><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://manual.bandai-hobby.net/menus/detail/2938\">Manual</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>225 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/97/MG_Gundam_Barbatos_Lupus.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20251116203726\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Gundam Barbatos Lupus\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"79\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Gundam Barbatos Lupus.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Gundam_Barbatos_Lupus.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/9/97/MG_Gundam_Barbatos_Lupus.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20251116203726\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ASW-G-08_Gundam_Barbatos_Lupus\" title=\"ASW-G-08 Gundam Barbatos Lupus\">ASW-G-08 Gundam Barbatos Lupus</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_IRON-BLOODED_ORPHANS\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS\">Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,500\n</td>\n<td>2025 November\n</td>\n<td>Parts variant of MG-212. Released to commemorate the 10th anniversary of <i>Gundam Iron-Blooded Orphans</i>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MG #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>226 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/FullAmorZZVerKa.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20260215075057\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"FullAmorZZVerKa\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"FullAmorZZVerKa.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"FullAmorZZVerKa.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/26/FullAmorZZVerKa.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20260215075057\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/FA-010S_Full_Armor_ZZ_Gundam\" title=\"FA-010S Full Armor ZZ Gundam\">FA-010S Full Armor ZZ Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_ZZ\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ\">Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a511,400\n</td>\n<td>2026 February\n</td>\n<td>Parts and color variant of MG-213; redesign of MG-030 with improved articulation and proportions. Removal of full armor parts reveals <a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-010S_Enhanced_ZZ_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-010S Enhanced ZZ Gundam\">Enhanced ZZ Gundam</a> underneath. Uses F1, F2, Z, and parts of I runners from MG-198. Features new Wing Shield connector parts for full armor parts attachment without par