MF-X13A Providence Gundam\">ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam</a> [Cross Contrast Colors/Clear Red]\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>RMB\u00a5435\n</td>\n<td>2024 May\n</td>\n<td>Tmall.com and JD.com exclusive clear red/red color variant of MG-196. Includes metallic silver water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/18/ZGMF-X09A_Justice_Gundam_%28Cross_Contrast_Colors-Clear_Yellow%29.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20240701073731\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam (Cross Contrast Colors-Clear Yellow)\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"125\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam (Cross Contrast Colors-Clear Yellow).jpg\" data-image-key=\"ZGMF-X09A_Justice_Gundam_%28Cross_Contrast_Colors-Clear_Yellow%29.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/1/18/ZGMF-X09A_Justice_Gundam_%28Cross_Contrast_Colors-Clear_Yellow%29.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20240701073731\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X09A_Justice_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam\">ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam</a> [Cross Contrast Colors/Clear Yellow]\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>RMB\u00a5420\n</td>\n<td>2024 May\n</td>\n<td>Tmall.com and JD.com exclusive clear turquoise/yellow color variant of MG-197. Includes metallic silver water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5c/MG_Musha_Gundam_Mk-II_Tokugawa_Ieyasu_Nanban-Dogusoku_Ver.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20240516025037\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG Musha Gundam Mk-II Tokugawa Ieyasu Nanban-Dogusoku Ver\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"80\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG Musha Gundam Mk-II Tokugawa Ieyasu Nanban-Dogusoku Ver.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_Musha_Gundam_Mk-II_Tokugawa_Ieyasu_Nanban-Dogusoku_Ver.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/5/5c/MG_Musha_Gundam_Mk-II_Tokugawa_Ieyasu_Nanban-Dogusoku_Ver.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20240516025037\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Musha_Gundam_Mk._II\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Musha Gundam Mk. II\">Musha Gundam Mk-II Tokugawa Ieyasu Nanban-Dogusoku Ver.</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Dynasty_Warriors_Gundam_2\" title=\"Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2\">Dynasty Warriors Gundam 2</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a57,000\n</td>\n<td>2024 May\n</td>\n<td>Nikk\u014d T\u014dshog\u016b, The Gundam Base and P-Bandai exclusive color variant of MG-133 with new head armor. Includes special decal sheet. Released to commemorate the 25th anniversary of <i>Shrines and Temples of Nikk\u014d</i> being listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/22/MG_F90N_Type_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20240806000303\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG F90N Type Boxart\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG F90N Type Boxart.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_F90N_Type_Boxart.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/22/MG_F90N_Type_Boxart.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20240806000303\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/F90N_Gundam_F90_Next_Type\" title=\"F90N Gundam F90 Next Type\">F90N Gundam F90 N-Type</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_F90:_Fastest_Formula\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam F90: Fastest Formula\">Mobile Suit Gundam F90: Fastest Formula</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,000\n</td>\n<td>2024 June\n</td>\n<td>P-Bandai exclusive color variant of MG F90 Gundam F90 with N-Type <a href=\"/wiki/Mission_Packs\" title=\"Mission Packs\">Mission Pack</a>; removal of Hull Fighter reveals <a href=\"/wiki/F90_Gundam_F90\" title=\"F90 Gundam F90\">F90-2 Gundam F90 Unit 2 (Roll Out Color)</a>. N-Type Mission Pack is compatible with other Mission Packs to create variants appeared in the manga<sup id=\"cite_ref-23\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-23\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>23<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup>. Includes water slide decal sheet and Action Base 4 (with one base plate instead of three). Released as part of P-Bandai's <a href=\"/wiki/F90_A_to_Z_PROJECT\" title=\"F90 A to Z PROJECT\">F90 A to Z Project</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td>The Gundam Base Limited <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X42S_Destiny_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X42S Destiny Gundam\">Destiny Gundam (Heine Westenfluss Custom)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,500\n</td>\n<td>2024 July\n</td>\n<td>The Gundam Base exclusive re-release of Gunpla Super Expo Tokyo 2010 exclusive MG ZGMF-X42S-REVOLUTION Destiny Gundam (<a href=\"/wiki/Heine_Westenfluss\" title=\"Heine Westenfluss\">Heine Westenfluss</a> Custom) with color variant of \"Wing of Light\" effect parts, as well as Beam Palm and Beam Boomerang effect parts from MG ZGMF-X42S Destiny Gundam Extreme Blast Mode. Includes custom display base and water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td><span class=\"new\" title=\"RX-78TB-4\uff3bPF\uff3d Gundam Stormbringer P.F. (page does not exist)\" data-uncrawlable-url=\"L3dpa2kvUlgtNzhUQi00JUVGJUJDJUJCUEYlRUYlQkMlQkRfR3VuZGFtX1N0b3JtYnJpbmdlcl9QLkYuP2FjdGlvbj1lZGl0JnJlZGxpbms9MQ==\">RX-78TB-4[PF] Gundam Stormbringer P.F.</span>\n</td>\n<td><i><span class=\"new\" title=\"Gundam Build Divers Genius Head Line (page does not exist)\" data-uncrawlable-url=\"L3dpa2kvR3VuZGFtX0J1aWxkX0RpdmVyc19HZW5pdXNfSGVhZF9MaW5lP2FjdGlvbj1lZGl0JnJlZGxpbms9MQ==\">Gundam Build Divers Genius Head Line</span></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,900\n</td>\n<td>2024 August\n</td>\n<td>P-Bandai exclusive parts and color variant of MG <a href=\"/wiki/RX-78TB-3%EF%BC%BBFA%EF%BC%BD_Gundam_Stormbringer_F.A.\" title=\"RX-78TB-3\uff3bFA\uff3d Gundam Stormbringer F.A.\">RX-78TB-3[FA] Gundam Stormbringer F.A.</a>. Includes parts to create the head of <a href=\"/wiki/RGM-79TB-1%EF%BC%BBT%EF%BC%BD_GM_Turbulence\" title=\"RGM-79TB-1\uff3bT\uff3d GM Turbulence\">RGM-79TB-1[T] GM Turbulence</a>, as well as water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3e/MG_RX-78-3_G-3_Gundam_Ver.3.0.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20240906025304\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MG RX-78-3 G-3 Gundam Ver.3.0\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"126\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MG RX-78-3 G-3 Gundam Ver.3.0.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MG_RX-78-3_G-3_Gundam_Ver.3.0.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/3/3e/MG_RX-78-3_G-3_Gundam_Ver.3.0.jpg/revisio