 Barbatos Lupus\">Gundam Barbatos Lupus</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_IRON-BLOODED_ORPHANS\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS\">Mobile Suit Gundam IRON-BLOODED ORPHANS</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a52,700\n</td>\n<td>2026 February\n</td>\n<td>P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit for MG-225. Includes Valkyrja Buster Sword, two Arm Rocket Launchers, optional antenna and shoulder parts, effect parts, a clear display stand and water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mission_Packs\" title=\"Mission Packs\">Mission Pack</a> <a href=\"/wiki/F90IIIYX_Cluster_Gundam_Xtra_Type\" title=\"F90IIIYX Cluster Gundam Xtra Type\">X-Type</a> for <a href=\"/wiki/F90III-Y_Cluster_Gundam\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"F90III-Y Cluster Gundam\">F90IIIY Cluster Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Silhouette_Formula_91_in_UC_0123\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Silhouette Formula 91 in UC 0123\">Mobile Suit Gundam Silhouette Formula 91 in UC 0123</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a53,500\n</td>\n<td>2026 March\n</td>\n<td>P-Bandai exclusive accessory kit to convert MG F90IIIY Cluster Gundam into F90IIIYX Cluster Gundam Xtra Type. Includes two red Beam Shield effect parts. Fully transformable kit. Released as part of P-Bandai's <a href=\"/wiki/F90_A_to_Z_PROJECT\" title=\"F90 A to Z PROJECT\">F90 A to Z Project</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/XXXG-01SR_Gundam_Sandrock_EW\" title=\"XXXG-01SR Gundam Sandrock EW\">XXXG-01SR Gundam Sandrock EW (Armadillo Lizard Unit)</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Mobile_Report_Gundam_Wing_Endless_Waltz:_The_Glory_of_Losers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers\">New Mobile Report Gundam Wing Endless Waltz: The Glory of Losers</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a56,200\n</td>\n<td>2026 March\n</td>\n<td>P-Bandai exclusive re-release of MG-149 with Armadillo Lizard Unit. Includes water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X10A_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam\">PHANTACI Freedom Gundam Ver.J</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>RMB\u00a5676\n</td>\n<td>2026 May\n</td>\n<td>Tmall.com and JD.com exclusive color variant of MG-192.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td>Astray Gundam [Cross Contrast Colors/Wood Black]\n</td>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td>RMB\u00a5650\n</td>\n<td>2026 May\n</td>\n<td>Tmall.com and JD.com exclusive color variant of MG-125 with Caletvwlch from MG <a href=\"/wiki/MBF-P02_Gundam_Astray_Red_Dragon\" title=\"MBF-P02 Gundam Astray Red Dragon\">MBF-P02 Gundam Astray Red Dragon</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td>Astray Gundam [Cross Contrast Colors/Petal White]\n</td>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td>RMB\u00a5650\n</td>\n<td>2026 May\n</td>\n<td>Tmall.com and JD.com exclusive color variant of MG-184 with Tactical Arms from MG <a href=\"/wiki/MBF-02VV_Gundam_Astray_Turn_Red\" title=\"MBF-02VV Gundam Astray Turn Red\">MBF-02VV Gundam Astray Turn Red</a>.\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div></div><p>Yen price excluding 5% tax (8% from 2014 to 2019; 10% from 2019 October onwards).\n</p><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Master_Grade_Extreme\">Master Grade Extreme</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fgundam.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMaster_Grade%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D4&amp;uselang=en&amp;metadata=article-registration-edit-article-section\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\" aria-label=\"Sign in to edit\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"tabber wds-tabber\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__wrapper with-bottom-border\"><ul class=\"wds-tabs\"><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab wds-is-current\" data-hash=\"Regular_\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">Regular </a></div></li><li class=\"wds-tabs__tab\" data-hash=\"Exclusives\"><div class=\"wds-tabs__tab-label\"><a href=\"#\">Exclusives</a></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content wds-is-current\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MGEX #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Extreme Point\n</th>\n<th>Link\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>001 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/dc/MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20200824042830\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGEX Unicorn Gundam Ver.Ka\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGEX Unicorn Gundam Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/dc/MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.Ka.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20200824042830\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn_(Novel)\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn (Novel)\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i> (Novel)\n</td>\n<td>\u00a523,000\n</td>\n<td>2020 September\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-102 with improved articulation and proportions. Uses the N and O plate runners of MG-102, Q plate runner of MG-150, S, T, U and W plate runners of MG RX-0 Unicorn Gundam HD Color + MS Cage, and Emotion Manipulator SP (MP1) plate runner. Includes three Shield Funnels, MS Cage display stand, <a href=\"/wiki/Banagher_Links\" title=\"Banagher Links\">Banagher Links</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Audrey_Burne\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Audrey Burne\">Audrey Burne</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Marida_Cruz\" title=\"Marida Cruz\">Marida Cruz</a> and two <a href=\"/wiki/Cardeas_Vist\" title=\"Cardeas Vist\">Cardeas Vist</a> (standing and falling pose respectively) figurines, and water slide decal sheet. First Version <a href=\"/wiki/Hajime_Katoki\" title=\"Hajime Katoki\">Katoki</a> release of MGEX. Fully compatible with MG-150's full armor equipment.\n</td>\n<td>\"Extreme Luminous Mechanism\" - Flexible full-body LED unit that can change colors between red and green.\n</td>\n<td><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://manual.bandai-hobby.net/menus/detail/639\">Manual</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>002 <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d3/MGEX_Strike_Freedom_Gundam.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20221105094156\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGEX Strike Freedom Gundam\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"76\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGEX Strike Freedom Gundam.jpeg\" data-image-key=\"MGEX_Strike_Freedom_Gundam.jpeg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/d/d3/MGEX_Strike_Freedom_Gundam.jpeg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20221105094156\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X20A_Strike_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam</a>\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a514,000\n</td>\n<td>2022 November\n</td>\n<td>Redesign of MG-093 with improved articulation and proportions. Includes <a href=\"/wiki/Kira_Yamato\" title=\"Kira Yamato\">Kira Yamato</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Lacus_Clyne\" title=\"Lacus Clyne\">Lacus Clyne</a> figurines.\n</td>\n<td>\"Extreme Metallic Combination\" - Metallic Combination with 6 patterns (Copper gold coating, white gold coating, yellow gold coating, two different metallic molding colors, and etching decals).\n</td>\n<td><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://manual.bandai-hobby.net/menus/detail/646\">Manual</a>\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"wds-tab__content\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><table class=\"wikitable sortable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>MGEX #\n</th>\n<th>Model\n</th>\n<th>Series\n</th>\n<th>Yen Price\n</th>\n<th>Release Date\n</th>\n<th>Notes\n</th>\n<th>Extreme Point\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c9/MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.Ka_-Premium_Unicorn_Mode_Box-.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20200918055123\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGEX Unicorn Gundam Ver.Ka -Premium Unicorn Mode Box-\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGEX Unicorn Gundam Ver.Ka -Premium Unicorn Mode Box-.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.Ka_-Premium_Unicorn_Mode_Box-.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c9/MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.Ka_-Premium_Unicorn_Mode_Box-.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20200918055123\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a> [Premium \"Unicorn Mode\" Box]\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn_(Novel)\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn (Novel)\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i> (Novel)\n</td>\n<td>\u00a523,000\n</td>\n<td>2020 September / 2020 November (Gunpla Expo 2020)\n</td>\n<td>P-Bandai and GUNPLA EXPO TOKYO 2020 feat. GUNDAM conference exclusive re-release of MGEX-001 with exclusive box cover featuring Unicorn Gundam in Unicorn Mode.\n</td>\n<td>Extreme Luminous Mechanism\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A <figure class=\"mw-halign-right\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2d/MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.TWC.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20210507051228\" class=\"mw-file-description image\"><img alt=\"MGEX Unicorn Gundam Ver.TWC\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"100\" height=\"68\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"MGEX Unicorn Gundam Ver.TWC.jpg\" data-image-key=\"MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.TWC.jpg\" data-relevant=\"1\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/2/2d/MGEX_Unicorn_Gundam_Ver.TWC.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20210507051228\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td>\n<td>The Gundam Base Limited <a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam\">Unicorn Gundam</a> Ver.TWC\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_Unicorn\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn\">Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a525,000\n</td>\n<td>2020 December\n</td>\n<td>The Gundam Base exclusive re-release of MGEX-001 with a different backpack and new water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>Extreme Luminous Mechanism\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X20A_Strike_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam</a> [Midnight Coating]\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>RMB\u00a54,200\n</td>\n<td>2024 May\n</td>\n<td>Tmall.com and JD.com exclusive clear black/black color variant of MGEX-002. Includes black BA-13 Action Base 1 and water slide decal sheet.\n</td>\n<td>Metallic Combination with 5 patterns (Black metallic coating, black matt coating, black molding color, clear black and etching decals).\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X20A_Strike_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam</a> [Twilight Coating]\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a560,000\n</td>\n<td>2025 December\n</td>\n<td>Events and The Gundam Base exclusive white/light blue color variant of MGEX-002.\n</td>\n<td>N/A\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>N/A\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X20A_Strike_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam</a> [Mechanical Clear]\n</td>\n<td><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Destiny\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny</a></i>\n</td>\n<td>\u00a517,000\n</td>\n<td>2026 January\n</td>\n<td>P-Bandai exclusive re-release of MGEX-002 with clear armor parts.\n</td>\n<td>Extreme Metallic Combination\n</td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div></div><p>Yen price excluding 10% tax.\n</p><h2><span id=\"Notes_.26_Trivia\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes_&amp;_Trivia\">Notes &amp; Trivia</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fgundam.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMaster_Grade%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D5&amp;uselang=en&amp;metadata=article-registration-edit-article-section\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\" aria-label=\"Sign in to edit\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>MG kits from 1995 to 1998 included heavyuser parts that could be cemented to the armor panels for added detail.</li>\n<li>Older MG kits before 2006 that have been reissued in the 2010s use the 2006 SB-1 Beam Saber runner in place of the original runner. The original runner's mold has been decommissioned due to reaching its limit for usage.</li>\n<li>This grade introduced a trend of Gunpla kits being packaged in monochrome box covers when sold exclusively through Premium Bandai (P-Bandai). Most P-Bandai kits are variations of existing retail kits and lack the design budget associated with retail kits, so along with the monochrome box covers, these kits lack their own lore sections and artwork, but use composited photographs instead. They often also do not have their own manuals, but are packaged with the manual of the retail kit of which they are based on along with a loose supplementary page detailing the differences instead.\n<ul><li>The exceptions to these are \"Ver.Ka\" kits and other kits that are not derived from retail kits, such as <a href=\"/wiki/F90_Gundam_F90\" title=\"F90 Gundam F90\">F90 Gundam F90</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/F90II-I_Gundam_F90II_Intercept_Type\" title=\"F90II-I Gundam F90II Intercept Type\">F90II-I Gundam F90II I-Type</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/ORX-013_Gundam_Mk-V\" title=\"ORX-013 Gundam Mk-V\">ORX-013 Gundam Mk-V</a>. This indicates these kits might be planned as regular retail kits originally, or, at least, received a higher design budget comparable to those kits, unlike traditional P-Bandai products.</li>\n<li>Some kits are exclusive to P-Bandai in Japan only and are sold as regular retail kits in rest of the world. These kits receive the same treatment as any other regular retail kit.</li>\n<li>The remaining exceptions are other P-Bandai original releases or kits that feature an intermediate number of new molds or new design elements. They would have their own manuals and artwork, though all would still be in monochrome.</li></ul></li>\n<li>Reissues that bear the blue Bandai logo on the box covers are sometimes bundled with manuals that still use the red logo.</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/wiki/Regild_Century\" title=\"Regild Century\">Regild Century</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Ad_Stella\" title=\"Ad Stella\">Ad Stella</a> are the only major timelines to lack any Master Grade kits, though the Ad Stella timeline debuted in the sister line <a href=\"/wiki/Master_Grade_SD\" title=\"Master Grade SD\">Master Grade SD</a> on August 2025.</li>\n<li>Master Grade Extreme <a href=\"/wiki/RX-0_Unicorn_Gundam\" title=\"RX-0 Unicorn Gundam\">RX-0 Unicorn Gundam \"Ver.Ka\"</a> is the most expensive Master Grade regular release to date, while the exclusive MGEX <a href=\"/wiki/ZGMF-X20A_Strike_Freedom_Gundam\" title=\"ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam\">ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam</a> [Midnight Coating] is the overall most expensive Master Grade release to date.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fgundam.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMaster_Grade%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D6&amp;uselang=en&amp;metadata=article-registration-edit-article-section\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\" aria-label=\"Sign in to edit\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Master_Grade_SD\" title=\"Master Grade SD\">Master Grade SD</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Perfect_Grade\" title=\"Perfect Grade\">Perfect Grade</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hi-Resolution_Model\" title=\"Hi-Resolution Model\">Hi-Resolution Model</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Reborn-One_Hundred\" title=\"Reborn-One Hundred\">Reborn-One Hundred</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Full_Mechanics\" title=\"Full Mechanics\">Full Mechanics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Real_Grade\" title=\"Real Grade\">Real Grade</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/High_Grade\" title=\"High Grade\">High Grade</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Decal\" title=\"Gundam Decal\">Gundam Decal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Action_Base\" title=\"Action Base\">Action Base</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Yokohama_Walking_Gundam_Model_Series\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Yokohama Walking Gundam Model Series\">Yokohama Walking Gundam Model Series</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Front_Tokyo\" title=\"Gundam Front Tokyo\">Gundam Front Tokyo</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/The_Gundam_Base_Tokyo\" title=\"The Gundam Base Tokyo\">The Gundam Base Tokyo</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gundam_Side-F\" title=\"Gundam Side-F\">Gundam Side-F</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fgundam.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMaster_Grade%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D7&amp;uselang=en&amp;metadata=article-registration-edit-article-section\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\" aria-label=\"Sign in to edit\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://allthatgundam.web.fc2.com/gunpla/mg.htm\">Gundam Taizen - Master Grade</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://mgex.bandai-hobby.net/\">Bandai Hobby Site - Master Grade Extreme Official Page</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://bandai-hobby.net/notices/detail/34/\">Bandai Hobby Site - \u300cMG 1/100 \u30b8\u30e0\u30fb\u30b3\u30de\u30f3\u30c9(\u30b3\u30ed\u30cb\u30fc\u6226\u4ed5\u69d8)\u300d\u300cHGPG \u30d7\u30c1\u30c3\u30ac\u30a4 \u30b0\u30e9\u30cf\u30e0\u30a8\u30fc\u30ab\u30fc\u30db\u30ef\u30a4\u30c8\uff06\u30d7\u30e9\u30ab\u30fc\u30c9\u300d\u767a\u58f2\u6642\u671f\u5909\u66f4\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://bandai-hobby.net/notices/detail/50\">Bandai Hobby Site - \u300cMG 1/100 \u30ac\u30f3\u30c0\u30e0\u30d0\u30eb\u30d0\u30c8\u30b9\u300d\u767a\u58f2\u6642\u671f\u5909\u66f4\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://bandai-hobby.net/notices/detail/90/\">Bandai Hobby Site - \u300cMG 1/100 \u30bc\u30fc\u30bf\u30ac\u30f3\u30c0\u30e0 Ver.Ka\u300d\u767a\u58f2\u6708\u5909\u66f4\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/29216296@N00/4159874836\">Master Grade Gundam F90 \"prototype\" at Shizuoka - May 2006</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://kusakusa.wordpress.com/2008/05/18/47th-shizuoka-hobby-show/\">Kusakusa Gunpla - 47th Shizuoka Hobby Show</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gunjap.wordpress.com/2009/08/27/gundam-big-expo-strikes-back-limited-gunplas/\">gunjap - GUNDAM BIG EXPO Strikes Back!!! Limited Gunplas.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gunjap.net/site/?p=4760\">GUNJAP - MG 1/100 GN-X IV New Super Size Images</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-MG_AGE-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">\u2191 <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-MG_AGE_10-0\">10.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-MG_AGE_10-1\">10.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://gundamguy.blogspot.com/2012/11/mg-1100-gundam-age-3-normaln-age-fx-on.html\">Gundam Guy - MG 1/100 Gundam AGE-3 Normal and AGE-FX on Display @ Gunpla Expo World Tour 2012 Japan</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gunjap.net/site/?p=36260\">GUNJAP - MG 1/100 Gundam AGE-1 Normal Wallpaper Size Images + MG Titus, Spallow &amp; Gafran release dates</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Hangar\" should be used instead.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.gundam.info/news/gunpla/news_gunpla_20180411_02.html\">Gundam.Info</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-14\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-14\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Head, feet and Shield Booster from MG RX-121-2A Gundam TR-1 [Advanced Hazel].</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-15\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-15\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">By switching armor parts between a RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.3.0 [Solid Clear/Standard] and a RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.3.0 [Solid Clear/Reverse], two MG RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.3.0 (both without Core Fighters) can be rebuilt, one with standard armors and one with complete clear color armors.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-16\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-16\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">By switching armor parts between a RX-78-02 Gundam The Origin [Solid Clear/Standard] and a RX-78-02 Gundam The Origin [Solid Clear/Reverse], two MG RX-78-02 Gundam The Origin can be rebuilt, one with standard armors and one with complete clear color armors.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-COVID19_GBT_1-17\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-COVID19_GBT_1_17-0\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.gundam-base.net/news/10923.html\">THE GUNDAM BASE \u5e97\u8217\u4f11\u696d\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b\u53ca\u3073\u9650\u5b9a\u5546\u54c1\u7b49\u5e97\u982d\u767a\u58f2\u5ef6\u671f\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-18\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-18\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">By switching armor parts between a RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.2.0 Solid Clear Standard and a RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.2.0 Solid Clear Reverse, two MG RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.2.0 can be rebuilt, one with standard armors and one with complete clear color armors.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-19\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-19\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://bandai-hobby.net/notices/detail/60/\">Bandai Hobby Site - \uff3b\u304a\u8a6b\u3073\u3068\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b\uff3d10\u6708\u304b\u308912\u6708\u767a\u58f2\u4e88\u5b9a\u5546\u54c1\u306e\u767a\u58f2\u5ef6\u671f\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-20\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-20\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Head parts, feet parts and Sub Arm Unit from MG RX-121-2A Gundam TR-1 [Advanced Hazel], Tri Booster Unit from MG RX-121-2 Gundam TR-1 [Hazel II] Early Type, and Long Blade Rifle from MG FF-X29A G-Parts [Hrududu].</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-21\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-21\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">By switching armor parts between a GN-001 Gundam Exia Solid Clear and a GN-001 Gundam Exia Solid Clear Another, two MG GN-001 Gundam Exia can be rebuilt, one with standard armors and one with complete clear color armors.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-22\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-22\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">By switching armor parts between a GAT-X105 Aile Strike Gundam Ver.RM Solid Clear and a GAT-X105 Aile Strike Gundam Ver.RM Solid Clear Another, two MG GAT-X105 Aile Strike Gundam Ver.RM can be rebuilt, one with standard armors and one with complete clear color armors.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-23\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-23\">\u2191</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">F90NA Gundam F90 NA-Type, F90NB Gundam F90 NB-Type, F90ND Gundam F90 ND-Type, F90NE Gundam F90 NE-Type, F90NF Gundam F90 NF-Type, F90NG Gundam F90 NG-Type, F90NV Gundam F90 NV-Type and F90NGVW Gundam F90 NGVW-Type</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fgundam.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FMaster_Grade%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D8&amp;uselang=en&amp;metadata=article-registration-edit-article-section\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\" aria-label=\"Sign in to edit\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-tiny\" aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\"><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-pencil-tiny\"></use></svg></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a target=\"_b